9// This provides C++ code generation targeting the Itanium C++ ABI. The class
10// in this file generates structures that follow the Itanium C++ ABI, which is
11// documented at:
12// http://www.codesourcery.com/public/cxx-abi/abi.html
13// http://www.codesourcery.com/public/cxx-abi/abi-eh.html
14//
15// It also supports the closely-related ARM ABI, documented at:
16// http://infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.doc.ihi0041c/IHI0041C_cppabi.pdf
17//
18//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

73 bool isThisCompleteObject(GlobalDecl GD) const override {
74 // The Itanium ABI has separate complete-object vs. base-object
75 // variants of both constructors and destructors.
76 if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
77 switch (GD.getDtorType()) {
78 case Dtor_Complete:
79 case Dtor_Deleting:
80 return true;
81
82 case Dtor_Base:
83 return false;
84
85 case Dtor_Comdat:
86 llvm_unreachable("emitting dtor comdat as function?");
87 }
88 llvm_unreachable("bad dtor kind");
89 }
90 if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
91 switch (GD.getCtorType()) {
92 case Ctor_Complete:
93 return true;
94
95 case Ctor_Base:
96 return false;
97
98 case Ctor_CopyingClosure:
99 case Ctor_DefaultClosure:
100 llvm_unreachable("closure ctors in Itanium ABI?");
101
102 case Ctor_Comdat:
103 llvm_unreachable("emitting ctor comdat as function?");
104 }
105 llvm_unreachable("bad dtor kind");
106 }
107
108 // No other kinds.
109 return false;
110 }

337 /**************************** RTTI Uniqueness ******************************/
338
339protected:
340 /// Returns true if the ABI requires RTTI type_info objects to be unique
341 /// across a program.
342 virtual bool shouldRTTIBeUnique() const { return true; }
343
344public:
345 /// What sort of unique-RTTI behavior should we use?
346 enum RTTIUniquenessKind {
347 /// We are guaranteeing, or need to guarantee, that the RTTI string
348 /// is unique.
349 RUK_Unique,
350
351 /// We are not guaranteeing uniqueness for the RTTI string, so we
352 /// can demote to hidden visibility but must use string comparisons.
353 RUK_NonUniqueHidden,
354
355 /// We are not guaranteeing uniqueness for the RTTI string, so we
356 /// have to use string comparisons, but we also have to emit it with
357 /// non-hidden visibility.
358 RUK_NonUniqueVisible
359 };
360
361 /// Return the required visibility status for the given type and linkage in
362 /// the current ABI.
363 RTTIUniquenessKind
364 classifyRTTIUniqueness(QualType CanTy,
365 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage) const;
366 friend class ItaniumRTTIBuilder;
367
368 void emitCXXStructor(GlobalDecl GD) override;
369
370 std::pair<llvm::Value *, const CXXRecordDecl *>
371 LoadVTablePtr(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address This,
372 const CXXRecordDecl *RD) override;
373
374 private:
375 bool hasAnyUnusedVirtualInlineFunction(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
376 const auto &VtableLayout =
377 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
378
379 for (const auto &VtableComponent : VtableLayout.vtable_components()) {
380 // Skip empty slot.
381 if (!VtableComponent.isUsedFunctionPointerKind())
382 continue;
383
384 const CXXMethodDecl *Method = VtableComponent.getFunctionDecl();
385 if (!Method->getCanonicalDecl()->isInlined())
386 continue;
387
388 StringRef Name = CGM.getMangledName(VtableComponent.getGlobalDecl());
389 auto *Entry = CGM.GetGlobalValue(Name);
390 // This checks if virtual inline function has already been emitted.
391 // Note that it is possible that this inline function would be emitted
392 // after trying to emit vtable speculatively. Because of this we do
393 // an extra pass after emitting all deferred vtables to find and emit
394 // these vtables opportunistically.
395 if (!Entry || Entry->isDeclaration())
396 return true;
397 }
398 return false;
399 }
400
401 bool isVTableHidden(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
402 const auto &VtableLayout =
403 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
404
405 for (const auto &VtableComponent : VtableLayout.vtable_components()) {
406 if (VtableComponent.isRTTIKind()) {
407 const CXXRecordDecl *RTTIDecl = VtableComponent.getRTTIDecl();
408 if (RTTIDecl->getVisibility() == Visibility::HiddenVisibility)
409 return true;
410 } else if (VtableComponent.isUsedFunctionPointerKind()) {
411 const CXXMethodDecl *Method = VtableComponent.getFunctionDecl();
412 if (Method->getVisibility() == Visibility::HiddenVisibility &&
413 !Method->isDefined())
414 return true;
415 }
416 }
417 return false;
418 }

473CodeGen::CGCXXABI *CodeGen::CreateItaniumCXXABI(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
474 switch (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().getKind()) {
475 // For IR-generation purposes, there's no significant difference
476 // between the ARM and iOS ABIs.
477 case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
478 case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
479 case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
480 return new ARMCXXABI(CGM);
481
482 case TargetCXXABI::iOS64:
483 return new iOS64CXXABI(CGM);
484
485 // Note that AArch64 uses the generic ItaniumCXXABI class since it doesn't
486 // include the other 32-bit ARM oddities: constructor/destructor return values
487 // and array cookies.
488 case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
489 return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /* UseARMMethodPtrABI = */ true,
490 /* UseARMGuardVarABI = */ true);
491
492 case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
493 return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /* UseARMMethodPtrABI = */ true);
494
495 case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
496 return new WebAssemblyCXXABI(CGM);
497
498 case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
499 if (CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch()
500 == llvm::Triple::le32) {
501 // For PNaCl, use ARM-style method pointers so that PNaCl code
502 // does not assume anything about the alignment of function
503 // pointers.
504 return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM, /* UseARMMethodPtrABI = */ true,
505 /* UseARMGuardVarABI = */ false);
506 }
507 return new ItaniumCXXABI(CGM);
508
509 case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
510 llvm_unreachable("Microsoft ABI is not Itanium-based");
511 }
512 llvm_unreachable("bad ABI kind");
513}

515llvm::Type *
516ItaniumCXXABI::ConvertMemberPointerType(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
517 if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
518 return CGM.PtrDiffTy;
519 if (getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
520 return llvm::StructType::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
521 }
522 return llvm::StructType::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
523}
524
525/// In the Itanium and ARM ABIs, method pointers have the form:
526/// struct { ptrdiff_t ptr; ptrdiff_t adj; } memptr;
527///
528/// In the Itanium ABI:
529/// - method pointers are virtual if (memptr.ptr & 1) is nonzero
530/// - the this-adjustment is (memptr.adj)
531/// - the virtual offset is (memptr.ptr - 1)
532///
533/// In the ARM ABI:
534/// - method pointers are virtual if (memptr.adj & 1) is nonzero
535/// - the this-adjustment is (memptr.adj >> 1)
536/// - the virtual offset is (memptr.ptr)
537/// ARM uses 'adj' for the virtual flag because Thumb functions
538/// may be only single-byte aligned.
539///
540/// XXXAR: TODO: add a CHERI ABI similar to ARM but using tag bit
541///
542/// If the member is virtual, the adjusted 'this' pointer points
543/// to a vtable pointer from which the virtual offset is applied.
544///
545/// If the member is non-virtual, memptr.ptr is the address of
546/// the function to call.
547CGCallee ItaniumCXXABI::EmitLoadOfMemberFunctionPointer(
548 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, Address ThisAddr,
549 llvm::Value *&ThisPtrForCall,
550 llvm::Value *MemFnPtr, const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
551 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
552
553 const FunctionProtoType *FPT =
554 MPT->getPointeeType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
555 const CXXRecordDecl *RD =
556 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(MPT->getClass()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
557
558 llvm::FunctionType *FTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(
559 CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodType(RD, FPT, /*FD=*/nullptr));
560
561 llvm::Constant *ptrdiff_1 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 1);
562
563 llvm::BasicBlock *FnVirtual = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.virtual");
564 llvm::BasicBlock *FnNonVirtual = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.nonvirtual");
565 llvm::BasicBlock *FnEnd = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.end");
566
567 // Extract memptr.adj, which is in the second field.
568 llvm::Value *RawAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemFnPtr, 1, "memptr.adj");
569
570 // Compute the true adjustment.
571 llvm::Value *Adj = RawAdj;
572 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI)
573 Adj = Builder.CreateAShr(Adj, ptrdiff_1, "memptr.adj.shifted");
574
575 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
576 // Apply the adjustment and cast back to the original struct type
577 // for consistency.
578 llvm::Value *This = ThisAddr.getPointer();
579 llvm::Value *VTableAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(This, CGM.Int8PtrTy,
580 "this.not.adjusted");
581 VTableAddr = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(VTableAddr, Adj, "memptr.vtable.addr");
582 This = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTableAddr, This->getType(), "this.adjusted");
583 ThisPtrForCall = This;
584
585 // Load the function pointer.
586 llvm::Value *FnPtr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemFnPtr, 0, "memptr.ptr");
587
588 // If the LSB in the function pointer is 1, the function pointer points to
589 // a virtual function.
590 // TODO: use new CHERI CXX ABI
591 bool IsCheriABI = getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities();
592 llvm::Value *IsVirtual;
593 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI || IsCheriABI) // XXXAR: TODO: use tag bit instead
594 IsVirtual = Builder.CreateAnd(RawAdj, ptrdiff_1);
595 else {
596 IsVirtual = Builder.CreateAnd(FnPtr, ptrdiff_1);
597 }
598 IsVirtual = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(IsVirtual, "memptr.isvirtual");
599 Builder.CreateCondBr(IsVirtual, FnVirtual, FnNonVirtual);
600
601 // In the virtual path, the adjustment left 'This' pointing to the
602 // vtable of the correct base subobject. The "function pointer" is an
603 // offset within the vtable (+1 for the virtual flag on non-ARM).
604 CGF.EmitBlock(FnVirtual);
605
606 // Cast the adjusted this to a pointer to vtable pointer and load.
607 llvm::Type *VTableTy = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
608 CharUnits VTablePtrAlign =
609 CGF.CGM.getDynamicOffsetAlignment(ThisAddr.getAlignment(), RD,
610 CGF.getPointerAlign());
611 llvm::Value *VTable =
612 CGF.GetVTablePtr(Address(VTableAddr, VTablePtrAlign), VTableTy, RD);
613
614 // Apply the offset.
615 // On ARM64, to reserve extra space in virtual member function pointers,
616 // we only pay attention to the low 32 bits of the offset.
617 llvm::Value *VTableOffset =
618 Builder.CreatePtrToInt(FnPtr, CGM.PtrDiffTy, "memptr.vtable.offset");
619 if (!UseARMMethodPtrABI)
620 VTableOffset = Builder.CreateSub(VTableOffset, ptrdiff_1);
621 if (Use32BitVTableOffsetABI) {
622 VTableOffset = Builder.CreateTrunc(VTableOffset, CGF.Int32Ty);
623 VTableOffset = Builder.CreateZExt(VTableOffset, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
624 }
625 // Compute the address of the virtual function pointer.
626 llvm::Value *VFPAddr = Builder.CreateGEP(VTable, VTableOffset);
627
628 // Check the address of the function pointer if CFI on member function
629 // pointers is enabled.
630 llvm::Constant *CheckSourceLocation;
631 llvm::Constant *CheckTypeDesc;
632 bool ShouldEmitCFICheck = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall) &&
633 CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD);
634 if (ShouldEmitCFICheck) {
635 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
636
637 CheckSourceLocation = CGF.EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc());
638 CheckTypeDesc = CGF.EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(MPT, 0));
639 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
640 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_VMFCall),
641 CheckSourceLocation,
642 CheckTypeDesc,
643 };
644
645 llvm::Metadata *MD =
646 CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForVirtualMemPtrType(QualType(MPT, 0));
647 llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), MD);
648
649 llvm::Value *TypeTest = Builder.CreateCall(
650 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {VFPAddr, TypeId});
651
652 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall)) {
653 CGF.EmitTrapCheck(TypeTest);
654 } else {
655 llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
656 CGM.getLLVMContext(),
657 llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
658 llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateCall(
659 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {VTable, AllVtables});
660 CGF.EmitCheck(std::make_pair(TypeTest, SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall),
661 SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
662 {VTable, ValidVtable});
663 }
664
665 FnVirtual = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
666 }
667
668 // Load the virtual function to call.
669 VFPAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(VFPAddr, FTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS)->getPointerTo(DefaultAS));
670 llvm::Value *VirtualFn = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
671 VFPAddr, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "memptr.virtualfn");
672 CGF.EmitBranch(FnEnd);
673
674 // In the non-virtual path, the function pointer is actually a
675 // function pointer.
676 CGF.EmitBlock(FnNonVirtual);
677 llvm::Value *NonVirtualFn;
678 if (IsCheriABI) {
679 NonVirtualFn = Builder.CreatePointerCast(FnPtr, FTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS),
680 "memptr.nonvirtualfn");
681 } else {
682 NonVirtualFn = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(FnPtr, FTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS),
683 "memptr.nonvirtualfn");
684 }
685
686 // Check the function pointer if CFI on member function pointers is enabled.
687 if (ShouldEmitCFICheck) {
688 CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getClass()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
689 if (RD->hasDefinition()) {
690 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
691
692 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
693 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_NVMFCall),
694 CheckSourceLocation,
695 CheckTypeDesc,
696 };
697
698 llvm::Value *Bit = Builder.getFalse();
699 llvm::Value *CastedNonVirtualFn =
700 Builder.CreateBitCast(NonVirtualFn, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
701 for (const CXXRecordDecl *Base : CGM.getMostBaseClasses(RD)) {
702 llvm::Metadata *MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(
703 getContext().getMemberPointerType(
704 MPT->getPointeeType(),
705 getContext().getRecordType(Base).getTypePtr()));
706 llvm::Value *TypeId =
707 llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), MD);
708
709 llvm::Value *TypeTest =
710 Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
711 {CastedNonVirtualFn, TypeId});
712 Bit = Builder.CreateOr(Bit, TypeTest);
713 }
714
715 CGF.EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Bit, SanitizerKind::CFIMFCall),
716 SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
717 {CastedNonVirtualFn, llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.IntPtrTy)});
718
719 FnNonVirtual = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
720 }
721 }
722
723 // We're done.
724 CGF.EmitBlock(FnEnd);
725 llvm::PHINode *CalleePtr = Builder.CreatePHI(FTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS), 2);
726 CalleePtr->addIncoming(VirtualFn, FnVirtual);
727 CalleePtr->addIncoming(NonVirtualFn, FnNonVirtual);
728
729 CGCallee Callee(FPT, CalleePtr);
730 return Callee;
731}

733/// Compute an l-value by applying the given pointer-to-member to a
734/// base object.
735llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberDataPointerAddress(
736 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, Address Base, llvm::Value *MemPtr,
737 const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
738 assert(MemPtr->getType() == CGM.PtrDiffTy);
739
740 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
741
742 // Cast to char*.
743 Base = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Base, CGF.Int8Ty);
744
745 // Apply the offset, which we assume is non-null.
746 llvm::Value *Addr =
747 Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Base.getPointer(), MemPtr, "memptr.offset");
748
749 // Cast the address to the appropriate pointer type, adopting the
750 // address space of the base pointer.
751 llvm::Type *PType = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(MPT->getPointeeType())
752 ->getPointerTo(Base.getAddressSpace());
753 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, PType);
754}
755
756/// Perform a bitcast, derived-to-base, or base-to-derived member pointer
757/// conversion.
758///
759/// Bitcast conversions are always a no-op under Itanium.
760///
761/// Obligatory offset/adjustment diagram:
762/// <-- offset --> <-- adjustment -->
763/// |--------------------------|----------------------|--------------------|
764/// ^Derived address point ^Base address point ^Member address point
765///
766/// So when converting a base member pointer to a derived member pointer,
767/// we add the offset to the adjustment because the address point has
768/// decreased; and conversely, when converting a derived MP to a base MP
769/// we subtract the offset from the adjustment because the address point
770/// has increased.
771///
772/// The standard forbids (at compile time) conversion to and from
773/// virtual bases, which is why we don't have to consider them here.
774///
775/// The standard forbids (at run time) casting a derived MP to a base
776/// MP when the derived MP does not point to a member of the base.
777/// This is why -1 is a reasonable choice for null data member
778/// pointers.
779llvm::Value *
780ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerConversion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
781 const CastExpr *E,
782 llvm::Value *src) {
783 assert(E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer ||
784 E->getCastKind() == CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer ||
785 E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer);
786
787 // XXXAR: FIXME: CHERI
788
789 // Under Itanium, reinterprets don't require any additional processing.
790 if (E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer) return src;
791
792 // Use constant emission if we can.
793 if (isa<llvm::Constant>(src))
794 return EmitMemberPointerConversion(E, cast<llvm::Constant>(src));
795
796 llvm::Constant *adj = getMemberPointerAdjustment(E);
797 if (!adj) return src;
798
799 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
800 bool isDerivedToBase = (E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer);
801
802 const MemberPointerType *destTy =
803 E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
804
805 // For member data pointers, this is just a matter of adding the
806 // offset if the source is non-null.
807 if (destTy->isMemberDataPointer()) {
808 llvm::Value *dst;
809 if (isDerivedToBase)
810 dst = Builder.CreateNSWSub(src, adj, "adj");
811 else
812 dst = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(src, adj, "adj");
813
814 // Null check.
815 llvm::Value *null = llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(src->getType());
816 llvm::Value *isNull = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(src, null, "memptr.isnull");
817 return Builder.CreateSelect(isNull, src, dst);
818 }
819
820 // The this-adjustment is left-shifted by 1 on ARM.
821 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
822 uint64_t offset = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(adj)->getZExtValue();
823 offset <<= 1;
824 adj = llvm::ConstantInt::get(adj->getType(), offset);
825 }
826
827 llvm::Value *srcAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(src, 1, "src.adj");
828 llvm::Value *dstAdj;
829 if (isDerivedToBase)
830 dstAdj = Builder.CreateNSWSub(srcAdj, adj, "adj");
831 else
832 dstAdj = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(srcAdj, adj, "adj");
833
834 return Builder.CreateInsertValue(src, dstAdj, 1);
835}
836
837llvm::Constant *
838ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerConversion(const CastExpr *E,
839 llvm::Constant *src) {
840 assert(E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer ||
841 E->getCastKind() == CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer ||
842 E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer);
843
844 // XXXAR: FIXME: CHERI
845
846 // Under Itanium, reinterprets don't require any additional processing.
847 if (E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer) return src;
848
849 // If the adjustment is trivial, we don't need to do anything.
850 llvm::Constant *adj = getMemberPointerAdjustment(E);
851 if (!adj) return src;
852
853 bool isDerivedToBase = (E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer);
854
855 const MemberPointerType *destTy =
856 E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
857
858 // For member data pointers, this is just a matter of adding the
859 // offset if the source is non-null.
860 if (destTy->isMemberDataPointer()) {
861 // null maps to null.
862 if (src->isAllOnesValue()) return src;
863
864 if (isDerivedToBase)
865 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWSub(src, adj);
866 else
867 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWAdd(src, adj);
868 }
869
870 // The this-adjustment is left-shifted by 1 on ARM.
871 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
872 uint64_t offset = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(adj)->getZExtValue();
873 offset <<= 1;
874 adj = llvm::ConstantInt::get(adj->getType(), offset);
875 }
876
877 llvm::Constant *srcAdj = llvm::ConstantExpr::getExtractValue(src, 1);
878 llvm::Constant *dstAdj;
879 if (isDerivedToBase)
880 dstAdj = llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWSub(srcAdj, adj);
881 else
882 dstAdj = llvm::ConstantExpr::getNSWAdd(srcAdj, adj);
883
884 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getInsertValue(src, dstAdj, 1);
885}

887llvm::Constant *
888ItaniumCXXABI::EmitNullMemberPointer(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
889 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
890 // A NULL pointer is represented as -1.
891 if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
892 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, -1ULL, /*isSigned=*/true);
893
894 llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 0);
895 llvm::Constant *Null =
896 CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities() ?
897 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy) : Zero;
898 llvm::Constant *Values[2] = { Null, Zero };
899 return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Values);
900}

904 CharUnits offset) {
905 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
906 // A pointer to data member is an offset from the base address of
907 // the class object containing it, represented as a ptrdiff_t
908 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, offset.getQuantity());
909}

922
923llvm::Value *
924ItaniumCXXABI::BuildMemberPointer(const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
925 CharUnits ThisAdjustment,
926 CodeGenFunction* CGF) {
927 assert(MD->isInstance() && "Member function must not be static!");
928
929 CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
930 const TargetInfo& TI = CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo();
931
932 // Get the function pointer (or index if this is a virtual function).
933 llvm::Constant *MemPtr[2];
934 llvm::Value* NonConstAddr = nullptr;
935 if (MD->isVirtual()) {
936 uint64_t Index = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(MD);
937
938 const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
939 CharUnits PointerWidth =
940 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0));
941 uint64_t VTableOffset = (Index * PointerWidth.getQuantity());
942
943 auto getVtableOffsetAsPointer = [&](uint64_t Offset) {
944 llvm::Constant *Value = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, Offset);
945 if (TI.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
946 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(Value, CGM.VoidPtrTy);
947 }
948 return Value;
949 };
950 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
951 // ARM C++ ABI 3.2.1:
952 // This ABI specifies that adj contains twice the this
953 // adjustment, plus 1 if the member function is virtual. The
954 // least significant bit of adj then makes exactly the same
955 // discrimination as the least significant bit of ptr does for
956 // Itanium.
957 MemPtr[0] = getVtableOffsetAsPointer(VTableOffset);
958 MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
959 2 * ThisAdjustment.getQuantity() + 1);
960 } else {
961 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.3:
962 // For a virtual function, [the pointer field] is 1 plus the
963 // virtual table offset (in bytes) of the function,
964 // represented as a ptrdiff_t.
965 MemPtr[0] = getVtableOffsetAsPointer(VTableOffset + 1);
966 MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
967 ThisAdjustment.getQuantity());
968 }
969 } else {
970 const FunctionProtoType *FPT = MD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
971 llvm::Type *Ty;
972 // Check whether the function has a computable LLVM signature.
973 if (Types.isFuncTypeConvertible(FPT)) {
974 // The function has a computable LLVM signature; use the correct type.
975 Ty = Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(MD));
976 } else {
977 // Use an arbitrary non-function type to tell GetAddrOfFunction that the
978 // function type is incomplete.
979 Ty = CGM.PtrDiffTy;
980 }
981 llvm::Constant *addr = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(MD, Ty);
982
983 if (TI.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
984 if (CGF) {
985 // llvm::errs() << "emitting local member pointer to " << MD->getQualifiedNameAsString() << "\n";
986 NonConstAddr = CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(
987 *CGF, addr, CGM.VoidPtrTy);
988 }
989 else {
990 // llvm::errs() << "emitting global member pointer to " << MD->getQualifiedNameAsString() << "\n";
991 addr = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(addr, CGM.VoidPtrTy);
992 }
993 MemPtr[0] = addr;
994 } else {
995 MemPtr[0] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(addr, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
996 }
997 MemPtr[1] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy,
998 (UseARMMethodPtrABI ? 2 : 1) *
999 ThisAdjustment.getQuantity());
1000 }
1001 if (NonConstAddr) {
1002 auto MemPtrTy = llvm::StructType::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy, CGM.PtrDiffTy);
1003 auto Align = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(TI.getCHERICapabilityAlign());
1004 auto alloca = CGF->CreateTempAlloca(MemPtrTy, Align, "memptr_tmp");
1005 CGF->Builder.CreateStore(NonConstAddr, CGF->Builder.CreateStructGEP(alloca, 0));
1006 CGF->Builder.CreateStore(MemPtr[1], CGF->Builder.CreateStructGEP(alloca, 1));
1007 return CGF->Builder.CreateLoad(alloca);
1008 } else {
1009 auto Result = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(MemPtr, false);
1010 // TODO: how to set the required alignment?
1011 return Result;
1012 }
1013}

1017llvm::Constant *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointer(const APValue &MP,
1018 QualType MPType,
1019 CodeGenFunction* CGF) {
1020 const MemberPointerType *MPT = MPType->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
1021 const ValueDecl *MPD = MP.getMemberPointerDecl();
1022 if (!MPD)
1023 return EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
1024
1025 CharUnits ThisAdjustment = getMemberPointerPathAdjustment(MP);
1026
1027 if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(MPD))
1028 return cast<llvm::Constant>(BuildMemberPointer(MD, ThisAdjustment, CGF));
1029
1030 CharUnits FieldOffset =
1031 getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(getContext().getFieldOffset(MPD));
1032 return EmitMemberDataPointer(MPT, ThisAdjustment + FieldOffset);
1033}

1035/// The comparison algorithm is pretty easy: the member pointers are
1036/// the same if they're either bitwise identical *or* both null.
1037///
1038/// ARM is different here only because null-ness is more complicated.
1039llvm::Value *
1040ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerComparison(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1041 llvm::Value *L,
1042 llvm::Value *R,
1043 const MemberPointerType *MPT,
1044 bool Inequality) {
1045 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1046
1047 llvm::ICmpInst::Predicate Eq;
1048 llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps And, Or;
1049 if (Inequality) {
1050 Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
1051 And = llvm::Instruction::Or;
1052 Or = llvm::Instruction::And;
1053 } else {
1054 Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
1055 And = llvm::Instruction::And;
1056 Or = llvm::Instruction::Or;
1057 }
1058
1059 // Member data pointers are easy because there's a unique null
1060 // value, so it just comes down to bitwise equality.
1061 if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
1062 return Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, L, R);
1063
1064 // For member function pointers, the tautologies are more complex.
1065 // The Itanium tautology is:
1066 // (L == R) <==> (L.ptr == R.ptr && (L.ptr == 0 || L.adj == R.adj))
1067 // The ARM tautology is:
1068 // (L == R) <==> (L.ptr == R.ptr &&
1069 // (L.adj == R.adj ||
1070 // (L.ptr == 0 && ((L.adj|R.adj) & 1) == 0)))
1071 // The inequality tautologies have exactly the same structure, except
1072 // applying De Morgan's laws.
1073
1074 llvm::Value *LPtr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, 0, "lhs.memptr.ptr");
1075 llvm::Value *RPtr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, 0, "rhs.memptr.ptr");
1076
1077 // This condition tests whether L.ptr == R.ptr. This must always be
1078 // true for equality to hold.
1079 llvm::Value *PtrEq = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LPtr, RPtr, "cmp.ptr");
1080
1081 // This condition, together with the assumption that L.ptr == R.ptr,
1082 // tests whether the pointers are both null. ARM imposes an extra
1083 // condition.
1084 llvm::Value *Null = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LPtr->getType());
1085 llvm::Value *EqZero = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LPtr, Null, "cmp.ptr.null");
1086
1087 // This condition tests whether L.adj == R.adj. If this isn't
1088 // true, the pointers are unequal unless they're both null.
1089 llvm::Value *LAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, 1, "lhs.memptr.adj");
1090 llvm::Value *RAdj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, 1, "rhs.memptr.adj");
1091 llvm::Value *AdjEq = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LAdj, RAdj, "cmp.adj");
1092
1093 // XXXAR: we should just use the tag bit instead of checking low bit in adj
1094
1095 // Null member function pointers on ARM clear the low bit of Adj,
1096 // so the zero condition has to check that neither low bit is set.
1097 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
1098 llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 0);
1099 llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 1);
1100
1101 // Compute (l.adj | r.adj) & 1 and test it against zero.
1102 llvm::Value *OrAdj = Builder.CreateOr(LAdj, RAdj, "or.adj");
1103 llvm::Value *OrAdjAnd1 = Builder.CreateAnd(OrAdj, One);
1104 llvm::Value *OrAdjAnd1EqZero = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, OrAdjAnd1, Zero,
1105 "cmp.or.adj");
1106 EqZero = Builder.CreateBinOp(And, EqZero, OrAdjAnd1EqZero);
1107 }
1108
1109 // Tie together all our conditions.
1110 llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(Or, EqZero, AdjEq);
1111 Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(And, PtrEq, Result,
1112 Inequality ? "memptr.ne" : "memptr.eq");
1113 return Result;
1114}
1115
1116llvm::Value *
1117ItaniumCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1118 llvm::Value *MemPtr,
1119 const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
1120 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1121
1122 /// For member data pointers, this is just a check against -1.
1123 if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer()) {
1124 assert(MemPtr->getType() == CGM.PtrDiffTy);
1125 llvm::Value *NegativeOne =
1126 llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(MemPtr->getType());
1127 return Builder.CreateICmpNE(MemPtr, NegativeOne, "memptr.tobool");
1128 }
1129
1130 // In Itanium, a member function pointer is not null if 'ptr' is not null.
1131 llvm::Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, 0, "memptr.ptr");
1132 llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr, "memptr.tobool");
1133
1134 // XXXAR: we should just use the tag bit instead of checking adj
1135
1136 // On ARM, a member function pointer is also non-null if the low bit of 'adj'
1137 // (the virtual bit) is set.
1138 if (UseARMMethodPtrABI) {
1139 llvm::Value *Adj = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, 1, "memptr.adj");
1140 assert(Adj->getType() == CGM.PtrDiffTy);
1141 llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 0);
1142 llvm::Constant *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, 1);
1143 llvm::Value *VirtualBit = Builder.CreateAnd(Adj, One, "memptr.virtualbit");
1144 llvm::Value *IsVirtual = Builder.CreateICmpNE(VirtualBit, Zero,
1145 "memptr.isvirtual");
1146 Result = Builder.CreateOr(Result, IsVirtual, "memptr.isnonnull");
1147 }
1148
1149 return Result;
1150}
1151
1152bool ItaniumCXXABI::classifyReturnType(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1153 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = FI.getReturnType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1154 if (!RD)
1155 return false;
1156
1157 // If C++ prohibits us from making a copy, return by address.
1158 if (!RD->canPassInRegisters()) {
1159 auto Align = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(FI.getReturnType());
1160 FI.getReturnInfo() = ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(Align, /*ByVal=*/false);
1161 return true;
1162 }
1163 return false;
1164}

1171
1172/// The Itanium ABI always places an offset to the complete object
1173/// at entry -2 in the vtable.
1174void ItaniumCXXABI::emitVirtualObjectDelete(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1175 const CXXDeleteExpr *DE,
1176 Address Ptr,
1177 QualType ElementType,
1178 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor) {
1179 bool UseGlobalDelete = DE->isGlobalDelete();
1180 if (UseGlobalDelete) {
1181 // Derive the complete-object pointer, which is what we need
1182 // to pass to the deallocation function.
1183
1184 // Grab the vtable pointer as an intptr_t*.
1185 // XXXAR: is this correct or is it ptrdiff_t?
1186 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1187 auto *ClassDecl =
1188 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ElementType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1189 llvm::Value *VTable =
1190 CGF.GetVTablePtr(Ptr, CGF.PtrDiffTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS), ClassDecl);
1191
1192 // Track back to entry -2 and pull out the offset there.
1193 llvm::Value *OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(
1194 VTable, -2, "complete-offset.ptr");
1195 llvm::Value *Offset =
1196 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(OffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
1197
1198 // Apply the offset.
1199 llvm::Value *CompletePtr =
1200 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr.getPointer(), CGF.Int8PtrTy);
1201 CompletePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CompletePtr, Offset);
1202
1203 // If we're supposed to call the global delete, make sure we do so
1204 // even if the destructor throws.
1205 CGF.pushCallObjectDeleteCleanup(DE->getOperatorDelete(), CompletePtr,
1206 ElementType);
1207 }
1208
1209 // FIXME: Provide a source location here even though there's no
1210 // CXXMemberCallExpr for dtor call.
1211 CXXDtorType DtorType = UseGlobalDelete ? Dtor_Complete : Dtor_Deleting;
1212 EmitVirtualDestructorCall(CGF, Dtor, DtorType, Ptr, /*CE=*/nullptr);
1213
1214 if (UseGlobalDelete)
1215 CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
1216}

1218void ItaniumCXXABI::emitRethrow(CodeGenFunction &CGF, bool isNoReturn) {
1219 // void __cxa_rethrow();
1220
1221 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1222 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*IsVarArgs=*/false);
1223
1224 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_rethrow");
1225
1226 if (isNoReturn)
1227 CGF.EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn, None);
1228 else
1229 CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn);
1230}

1233 // void *__cxa_allocate_exception(size_t thrown_size);
1234
1235 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1236 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.SizeTy, /*IsVarArgs=*/false);

1241static llvm::FunctionCallee getThrowFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1242 // void __cxa_throw(void *thrown_exception, std::type_info *tinfo,
1243 // void (*dest) (void *));
1244
1245 llvm::Type *Args[3] = { CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy };
1246 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
1247 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, Args, /*IsVarArgs=*/false);
1248
1249 return CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_throw");

1251
1252void ItaniumCXXABI::emitThrow(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXThrowExpr *E) {
1253 QualType ThrowType = E->getSubExpr()->getType();
1254 // Now allocate the exception object.
1255 llvm::Type *SizeTy = CGF.ConvertType(getContext().getSizeType());
1256 uint64_t TypeSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ThrowType).getQuantity();
1257
1258 llvm::FunctionCallee AllocExceptionFn = getAllocateExceptionFn(CGM);
1259 llvm::CallInst *ExceptionPtr = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(
1260 AllocExceptionFn, llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, TypeSize), "exception");
1261
1262 CharUnits ExnAlign = CGF.getContext().getExnObjectAlignment();
1263 CGF.EmitAnyExprToExn(E->getSubExpr(), Address(ExceptionPtr, ExnAlign));
1264
1265 // Now throw the exception.
1266 llvm::Constant *TypeInfo = CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(ThrowType,
1267 /*ForEH=*/true);
1268
1269 // The address of the destructor. If the exception type has a
1270 // trivial destructor (or isn't a record), we just pass null.
1271 llvm::Value *Dtor = nullptr;
1272 if (const RecordType *RecordTy = ThrowType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1273 CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl());
1274 if (!Record->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
1275 CXXDestructorDecl *DtorD = Record->getDestructor();
1276 Dtor = CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(DtorD, Dtor_Complete));
1277 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities())
1278 Dtor = CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CGF, Dtor,
1279 CGM.Int8PtrTy);
1280 // Dtor = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Dtor, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
1281 Dtor = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Dtor, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
1282 }
1283 }
1284 if (!Dtor) Dtor = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
1285
1286 llvm::Value *args[] = { ExceptionPtr, TypeInfo, Dtor };
1287 CGF.EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(getThrowFn(CGM), args);
1288}
1289
1290static llvm::FunctionCallee getItaniumDynamicCastFn(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1291 // void *__dynamic_cast(const void *sub,
1292 // const abi::__class_type_info *src,
1293 // const abi::__class_type_info *dst,
1294 // std::ptrdiff_t src2dst_offset);
1295
1296 llvm::Type *Int8PtrTy = CGF.Int8PtrTy;
1297 llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
1298 CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1299
1300 llvm::Type *Args[4] = { Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy, PtrDiffTy };
1301
1302 llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(Int8PtrTy, Args, false);
1303
1304 // Mark the function as nounwind readonly.
1305 llvm::Attribute::AttrKind FuncAttrs[] = { llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind,
1306 llvm::Attribute::ReadOnly };
1307 llvm::AttributeList Attrs = llvm::AttributeList::get(
1308 CGF.getLLVMContext(), llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, FuncAttrs);
1309
1310 return CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__dynamic_cast", Attrs);
1311}

1313static llvm::FunctionCallee getBadCastFn(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1314 // void __cxa_bad_cast();
1315 llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, false);
1316 return CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__cxa_bad_cast");
1317}
1318
1319/// Compute the src2dst_offset hint as described in the
1320/// Itanium C++ ABI [2.9.7]
1321static CharUnits computeOffsetHint(ASTContext &Context,
1322 const CXXRecordDecl *Src,
1323 const CXXRecordDecl *Dst) {
1324 CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1325 /*DetectVirtual=*/false);
1326
1327 // If Dst is not derived from Src we can skip the whole computation below and
1328 // return that Src is not a public base of Dst. Record all inheritance paths.
1329 if (!Dst->isDerivedFrom(Src, Paths))
1330 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-2ULL);
1331
1332 unsigned NumPublicPaths = 0;
1333 CharUnits Offset;
1334
1335 // Now walk all possible inheritance paths.
1336 for (const CXXBasePath &Path : Paths) {
1337 if (Path.Access != AS_public) // Ignore non-public inheritance.
1338 continue;
1339
1340 ++NumPublicPaths;
1341
1342 for (const CXXBasePathElement &PathElement : Path) {
1343 // If the path contains a virtual base class we can't give any hint.
1344 // -1: no hint.
1345 if (PathElement.Base->isVirtual())
1346 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-1ULL);
1347
1348 if (NumPublicPaths > 1) // Won't use offsets, skip computation.
1349 continue;
1350
1351 // Accumulate the base class offsets.
1352 const ASTRecordLayout &L = Context.getASTRecordLayout(PathElement.Class);
1353 Offset += L.getBaseClassOffset(
1354 PathElement.Base->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
1355 }
1356 }
1357
1358 // -2: Src is not a public base of Dst.
1359 if (NumPublicPaths == 0)
1360 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-2ULL);
1361
1362 // -3: Src is a multiple public base type but never a virtual base type.
1363 if (NumPublicPaths > 1)
1364 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(-3ULL);
1365
1366 // Otherwise, the Src type is a unique public nonvirtual base type of Dst.
1367 // Return the offset of Src from the origin of Dst.
1368 return Offset;
1369}

1374

1390llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitTypeid(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1391 QualType SrcRecordTy,
1392 Address ThisPtr,
1393 llvm::Type *StdTypeInfoPtrTy) {

1395 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SrcRecordTy->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1396 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1397 llvm::Value *Value =
1398 CGF.GetVTablePtr(ThisPtr, StdTypeInfoPtrTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS),
1399 ClassDecl);
1400
1401 // Load the type info.
1402 Value = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(Value, -1ULL);
1403 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Value, CGF.getPointerAlign());

1410
1411llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitDynamicCastCall(
1412 CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address ThisAddr, QualType SrcRecordTy,
1413 QualType DestTy, QualType DestRecordTy, llvm::BasicBlock *CastEnd) {
1414 llvm::Type *PtrDiffLTy =
1415 CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1416 llvm::Type *DestLTy = CGF.ConvertType(DestTy);
1417
1418 llvm::Value *SrcRTTI =
1419 CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(SrcRecordTy.getUnqualifiedType());
1420 llvm::Value *DestRTTI =
1421 CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(DestRecordTy.getUnqualifiedType());
1422
1423 // Compute the offset hint.
1424 const CXXRecordDecl *SrcDecl = SrcRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1425 const CXXRecordDecl *DestDecl = DestRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1426 llvm::Value *OffsetHint = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1427 PtrDiffLTy,
1428 computeOffsetHint(CGF.getContext(), SrcDecl, DestDecl).getQuantity());
1429
1430 // Emit the call to __dynamic_cast.
1431 llvm::Value *Value = ThisAddr.getPointer();
1432 Value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(Value);
1433
1434 llvm::Value *args[] = {Value, SrcRTTI, DestRTTI, OffsetHint};
1435 Value = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getItaniumDynamicCastFn(CGF), args);
1436 Value = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, DestLTy);
1437
1438 /// C++ [expr.dynamic.cast]p9:
1439 /// A failed cast to reference type throws std::bad_cast
1440 if (DestTy->isReferenceType()) {
1441 llvm::BasicBlock *BadCastBlock =
1442 CGF.createBasicBlock("dynamic_cast.bad_cast");
1443
1444 llvm::Value *IsNull = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(Value);
1445 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNull, BadCastBlock, CastEnd);
1446
1447 CGF.EmitBlock(BadCastBlock);
1448 EmitBadCastCall(CGF);
1449 }
1450
1451 return Value;
1452}
1453
1454llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitDynamicCastToVoid(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1455 Address ThisAddr,
1456 QualType SrcRecordTy,
1457 QualType DestTy) {
1458 llvm::Type *PtrDiffLTy =
1459 CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1460 llvm::Type *DestLTy = CGF.ConvertType(DestTy);
1461
1462 auto *ClassDecl =
1463 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SrcRecordTy->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1464 // Get the vtable pointer.
1465 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1466 llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(ThisAddr, PtrDiffLTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS),
1467 ClassDecl);
1468
1469 // Get the offset-to-top from the vtable.
1470 llvm::Value *OffsetToTop =
1471 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(VTable, -2ULL);
1472 OffsetToTop =
1473 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(OffsetToTop, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
1474 "offset.to.top");
1475
1476 // Finally, add the offset to the pointer.
1477 llvm::Value *Value = ThisAddr.getPointer();
1478 Value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(Value);
1479 Value = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Value, OffsetToTop);
1480
1481 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, DestLTy);
1482}

1484bool ItaniumCXXABI::EmitBadCastCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1485 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = getBadCastFn(CGF);
1486 llvm::CallBase *Call = CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(Fn);
1487 Call->setDoesNotReturn();
1488 CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
1489 return true;
1490}

1492llvm::Value *
1493ItaniumCXXABI::GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1494 Address This,
1495 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
1496 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl) {
1497 llvm::Value *VTablePtr = CGF.GetVTablePtr(This, CGM.Int8PtrTy, ClassDecl);
1498 CharUnits VBaseOffsetOffset =
1499 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(ClassDecl,
1500 BaseClassDecl);
1501
1502 llvm::Value *VBaseOffsetPtr =
1503 CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_64(VTablePtr, VBaseOffsetOffset.getQuantity(),
1504 "vbase.offset.ptr");
1505 llvm::Value *VBaseOffset;
1506 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
1507 VBaseOffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(VBaseOffsetPtr,
1508 CGM.Int8PtrPtrTy);
1509 VBaseOffset =
1510 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VBaseOffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
1511 "vbase.offset.intcap");
1512 VBaseOffset = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(VBaseOffset);
1513 } else {
1514 VBaseOffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(VBaseOffsetPtr,
1515 CGM.PtrDiffTy->getPointerTo(
1516 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
1517
1518 VBaseOffset =
1519 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VBaseOffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
1520 "vbase.offset");
1521 }
1522
1523 return VBaseOffset;
1524}
1525
1526void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitCXXConstructors(const CXXConstructorDecl *D) {
1527 // Just make sure we're in sync with TargetCXXABI.
1528 assert(CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants());
1529
1530 // The constructor used for constructing this as a base class;
1531 // ignores virtual bases.
1532 CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Base));
1533
1534 // The constructor used for constructing this as a complete class;
1535 // constructs the virtual bases, then calls the base constructor.
1536 if (!D->getParent()->isAbstract()) {
1537 // We don't need to emit the complete ctor if the class is abstract.
1538 CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Complete));
1539 }
1540}
1541
1542CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgs
1543ItaniumCXXABI::buildStructorSignature(GlobalDecl GD,
1544 SmallVectorImpl<CanQualType> &ArgTys) {
1545 ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1546
1547 // All parameters are already in place except VTT, which goes after 'this'.
1548 // These are Clang types, so we don't need to worry about sret yet.
1549
1550 // Check if we need to add a VTT parameter (which has type void **).
1551 if ((isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl()) ? GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Base
1552 : GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base) &&
1553 cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl())->getParent()->getNumVBases() != 0) {
1554 ArgTys.insert(ArgTys.begin() + 1,
1555 Context.getPointerType(Context.VoidPtrTy));
1556 return AddedStructorArgs::prefix(1);
1557 }
1558 return AddedStructorArgs{};
1559}
1560
1561void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitCXXDestructors(const CXXDestructorDecl *D) {
1562 // The destructor used for destructing this as a base class; ignores
1563 // virtual bases.
1564 CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Base));
1565
1566 // The destructor used for destructing this as a most-derived class;
1567 // call the base destructor and then destructs any virtual bases.
1568 CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Complete));
1569
1570 // The destructor in a virtual table is always a 'deleting'
1571 // destructor, which calls the complete destructor and then uses the
1572 // appropriate operator delete.
1573 if (D->isVirtual())
1574 CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Deleting));
1575}
1576
1577void ItaniumCXXABI::addImplicitStructorParams(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1578 QualType &ResTy,
1579 FunctionArgList &Params) {
1580 const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl());
1581 assert(isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD));
1582
1583 // Check if we need a VTT parameter as well.
1584 if (NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD)) {
1585 ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1586
1587 // FIXME: avoid the fake decl
1588 QualType T = Context.getPointerType(Context.VoidPtrTy);
1589 auto *VTTDecl = ImplicitParamDecl::Create(
1590 Context, /*DC=*/nullptr, MD->getLocation(), &Context.Idents.get("vtt"),
1591 T, ImplicitParamDecl::CXXVTT);
1592 Params.insert(Params.begin() + 1, VTTDecl);
1593 getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) = VTTDecl;
1594 }
1595}
1596
1597void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitInstanceFunctionProlog(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1598 // Naked functions have no prolog.
1599 if (CGF.CurFuncDecl && CGF.CurFuncDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
1600 return;
1601
1602 /// Initialize the 'this' slot. In the Itanium C++ ABI, no prologue
1603 /// adjustments are required, because they are all handled by thunks.
1604 setCXXABIThisValue(CGF, loadIncomingCXXThis(CGF));
1605
1606 /// Initialize the 'vtt' slot if needed.
1607 if (getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)) {
1608 getStructorImplicitParamValue(CGF) = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
1609 CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)), "vtt");
1610 }
1611
1612 /// If this is a function that the ABI specifies returns 'this', initialize
1613 /// the return slot to 'this' at the start of the function.
1614 ///
1615 /// Unlike the setting of return types, this is done within the ABI
1616 /// implementation instead of by clients of CGCXXABI because:
1617 /// 1) getThisValue is currently protected
1618 /// 2) in theory, an ABI could implement 'this' returns some other way;
1619 /// HasThisReturn only specifies a contract, not the implementation
1620 if (HasThisReturn(CGF.CurGD))
1621 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(getThisValue(CGF), CGF.ReturnValue);
1622}
1623
1624CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgs ItaniumCXXABI::addImplicitConstructorArgs(
1625 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXConstructorDecl *D, CXXCtorType Type,
1626 bool ForVirtualBase, bool Delegating, CallArgList &Args) {
1627 if (!NeedsVTTParameter(GlobalDecl(D, Type)))
1628 return AddedStructorArgs{};
1629
1630 // Insert the implicit 'vtt' argument as the second argument.
1631 llvm::Value *VTT =
1632 CGF.GetVTTParameter(GlobalDecl(D, Type), ForVirtualBase, Delegating);
1633 QualType VTTTy = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1634 Args.insert(Args.begin() + 1, CallArg(RValue::get(VTT), VTTTy));
1635 return AddedStructorArgs::prefix(1); // Added one arg.
1636}
1637
1638void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitDestructorCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1639 const CXXDestructorDecl *DD,
1640 CXXDtorType Type, bool ForVirtualBase,
1641 bool Delegating, Address This) {
1642 GlobalDecl GD(DD, Type);
1643 llvm::Value *VTT = CGF.GetVTTParameter(GD, ForVirtualBase, Delegating);
1644 QualType VTTTy = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1645
1646 CGCallee Callee;
1647 if (getContext().getLangOpts().AppleKext &&
1648 Type != Dtor_Base && DD->isVirtual())
1649 Callee = CGF.BuildAppleKextVirtualDestructorCall(DD, Type, DD->getParent());
1650 else
1651 Callee = CGCallee::forDirect(CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GD), GD);
1652
1653 CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, This.getPointer(), VTT, VTTTy, nullptr);
1654}
1655
1656void ItaniumCXXABI::emitVTableDefinitions(CodeGenVTables &CGVT,
1657 const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1658 llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable = getAddrOfVTable(RD, CharUnits());
1659 if (VTable->hasInitializer())
1660 return;
1661
1662 ItaniumVTableContext &VTContext = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext();
1663 const VTableLayout &VTLayout = VTContext.getVTableLayout(RD);
1664 llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
1665 llvm::Constant *RTTI =
1666 CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(CGM.getContext().getTagDeclType(RD));
1667
1668 // Create and set the initializer.
1669 ConstantInitBuilder Builder(CGM);
1670 auto Components = Builder.beginStruct();
1671 CGVT.createVTableInitializer(Components, VTLayout, RTTI);
1672 Components.finishAndSetAsInitializer(VTable);
1673
1674 // Set the correct linkage.
1675 VTable->setLinkage(Linkage);
1676
1677 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && VTable->isWeakForLinker())
1678 VTable->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(VTable->getName()));
1679
1680 // Set the right visibility.
1681 CGM.setGVProperties(VTable, RD);
1682
1683 // If this is the magic class __cxxabiv1::__fundamental_type_info,
1684 // we will emit the typeinfo for the fundamental types. This is the
1685 // same behaviour as GCC.
1686 const DeclContext *DC = RD->getDeclContext();
1687 if (RD->getIdentifier() &&
1688 RD->getIdentifier()->isStr("__fundamental_type_info") &&
1689 isa<NamespaceDecl>(DC) && cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getIdentifier() &&
1690 cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)->getIdentifier()->isStr("__cxxabiv1") &&
1691 DC->getParent()->isTranslationUnit())
1692 EmitFundamentalRTTIDescriptors(RD);
1693
1694 if (!VTable->isDeclarationForLinker())
1695 CGM.EmitVTableTypeMetadata(VTable, VTLayout);
1696}

1698bool ItaniumCXXABI::isVirtualOffsetNeededForVTableField(
1699 CodeGenFunction &CGF, CodeGenFunction::VPtr Vptr) {
1700 if (Vptr.NearestVBase == nullptr)
1701 return false;
1702 return NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD);
1703}
1704
1705llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPointInStructor(
1706 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass, BaseSubobject Base,
1707 const CXXRecordDecl *NearestVBase) {
1708
1709 if ((Base.getBase()->getNumVBases() || NearestVBase != nullptr) &&
1710 NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD)) {
1711 return getVTableAddressPointInStructorWithVTT(CGF, VTableClass, Base,
1712 NearestVBase);
1713 }
1714 return getVTableAddressPoint(Base, VTableClass);
1715}
1716
1717llvm::Constant *
1718ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPoint(BaseSubobject Base,
1719 const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass) {
1720 llvm::GlobalValue *VTable = getAddrOfVTable(VTableClass, CharUnits());
1721
1722 // Find the appropriate vtable within the vtable group, and the address point
1723 // within that vtable.
1724 VTableLayout::AddressPointLocation AddressPoint =
1725 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext()
1726 .getVTableLayout(VTableClass)
1727 .getAddressPoint(Base);
1728 llvm::Value *Indices[] = {
1729 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 0),
1730 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, AddressPoint.VTableIndex),
1731 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, AddressPoint.AddressPointIndex),
1732 };
1733
1734 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(VTable->getValueType(), VTable,
1735 Indices, /*InBounds=*/true,
1736 /*InRangeIndex=*/1);
1737}
1738
1739llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPointInStructorWithVTT(
1740 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass, BaseSubobject Base,
1741 const CXXRecordDecl *NearestVBase) {
1742 assert((Base.getBase()->getNumVBases() || NearestVBase != nullptr) &&
1743 NeedsVTTParameter(CGF.CurGD) && "This class doesn't have VTT");
1744
1745 // Get the secondary vpointer index.
1746 uint64_t VirtualPointerIndex =
1747 CGM.getVTables().getSecondaryVirtualPointerIndex(VTableClass, Base);
1748
1749 /// Load the VTT.
1750 llvm::Value *VTT = CGF.LoadCXXVTT();
1751 if (VirtualPointerIndex)
1752 VTT = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(VTT, VirtualPointerIndex);
1753
1754 // And load the address point from the VTT.
1755 return CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VTT, CGF.getPointerAlign());
1756}
1757
1758llvm::Constant *ItaniumCXXABI::getVTableAddressPointForConstExpr(
1759 BaseSubobject Base, const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass) {
1760 return getVTableAddressPoint(Base, VTableClass);
1761}
1762
1763llvm::GlobalVariable *ItaniumCXXABI::getAddrOfVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
1764 CharUnits VPtrOffset) {
1765 assert(VPtrOffset.isZero() && "Itanium ABI only supports zero vptr offsets");
1766
1767 llvm::GlobalVariable *&VTable = VTables[RD];
1768 if (VTable)
1769 return VTable;
1770
1771 // Queue up this vtable for possible deferred emission.
1772 CGM.addDeferredVTable(RD);
1773
1774 SmallString<256> Name;
1775 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
1776 getMangleContext().mangleCXXVTable(RD, Out);
1777
1778 const VTableLayout &VTLayout =
1779 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVTableLayout(RD);
1780 llvm::Type *VTableType = CGM.getVTables().getVTableType(VTLayout);
1781
1782 // Use pointer alignment for the vtable. Otherwise we would align them based
1783 // on the size of the initializer which doesn't make sense as only single
1784 // values are read.
1785 unsigned PAlign = CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(0);
1786
1787 VTable = CGM.CreateOrReplaceCXXRuntimeVariable(
1788 Name, VTableType, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
1789 getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(PAlign).getQuantity());
1790 VTable->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
1791
1792 CGM.setGVProperties(VTable, RD);
1793
1794 return VTable;
1795}
1796
1797CGCallee ItaniumCXXABI::getVirtualFunctionPointer(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1798 GlobalDecl GD,
1799 Address This,
1800 llvm::Type *Ty,
1801 SourceLocation Loc) {
1802 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1803 Ty = Ty->getPointerTo(DefaultAS)->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
1804 auto *MethodDecl = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1805 llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(This, Ty, MethodDecl->getParent());
1806
1807 uint64_t VTableIndex = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(GD);
1808 llvm::Value *VFunc;
1809 if (CGF.ShouldEmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(MethodDecl->getParent())) {
1810 VFunc = CGF.EmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(
1811 MethodDecl->getParent(), VTable,
1812 VTableIndex * CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) / 8);
1813 } else {
1814 CGF.EmitTypeMetadataCodeForVCall(MethodDecl->getParent(), VTable, Loc);
1815
1816 llvm::Value *VFuncPtr =
1817 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(VTable, VTableIndex, "vfn");
1818 auto *VFuncLoad =
1819 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(VFuncPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
1820
1821 // Add !invariant.load md to virtual function load to indicate that
1822 // function didn't change inside vtable.
1823 // It's safe to add it without -fstrict-vtable-pointers, but it would not
1824 // help in devirtualization because it will only matter if we will have 2
1825 // the same virtual function loads from the same vtable load, which won't
1826 // happen without enabled devirtualization with -fstrict-vtable-pointers.
1827 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
1828 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers)
1829 VFuncLoad->setMetadata(
1830 llvm::LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load,
1831 llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
1832 llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Metadata *>()));
1833 VFunc = VFuncLoad;
1834 }
1835
1836 CGCallee Callee(GD, VFunc);
1837 return Callee;
1838}
1839
1840llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::EmitVirtualDestructorCall(
1841 CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor, CXXDtorType DtorType,
1842 Address This, const CXXMemberCallExpr *CE) {
1843 assert(CE == nullptr || CE->arg_begin() == CE->arg_end());
1844 assert(DtorType == Dtor_Deleting || DtorType == Dtor_Complete);
1845
1846 GlobalDecl GD(Dtor, DtorType);
1847 const CGFunctionInfo *FInfo =
1848 &CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXStructorDeclaration(GD);
1849 llvm::FunctionType *Ty = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(*FInfo);
1850 CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forVirtual(CE, GD, This, Ty);
1851
1852 CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, This.getPointer(), nullptr, QualType(),
1853 nullptr);
1854 return nullptr;
1855}

1862
1863bool ItaniumCXXABI::canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(
1864 const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
1865 // We don't emit available_externally vtables if we are in -fapple-kext mode
1866 // because kext mode does not permit devirtualization.
1867 if (CGM.getLangOpts().AppleKext)
1868 return false;
1869
1870 // If the vtable is hidden then it is not safe to emit an available_externally
1871 // copy of vtable.
1872 if (isVTableHidden(RD))
1873 return false;
1874
1875 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ForceEmitVTables)
1876 return true;
1877
1878 // If we don't have any not emitted inline virtual function then we are safe
1879 // to emit an available_externally copy of vtable.
1880 // FIXME we can still emit a copy of the vtable if we
1881 // can emit definition of the inline functions.
1882 if (hasAnyUnusedVirtualInlineFunction(RD))
1883 return false;
1884
1885 // For a class with virtual bases, we must also be able to speculatively
1886 // emit the VTT, because CodeGen doesn't have separate notions of "can emit
1887 // the vtable" and "can emit the VTT". For a base subobject, this means we
1888 // need to be able to emit non-virtual base vtables.
1889 if (RD->getNumVBases()) {
1890 for (const auto &B : RD->bases()) {
1891 auto *BRD = B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1892 assert(BRD && "no class for base specifier");
1893 if (B.isVirtual() || !BRD->isDynamicClass())
1894 continue;
1895 if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(BRD))
1896 return false;
1897 }
1898 }
1899
1900 return true;
1901}
1902
1903bool ItaniumCXXABI::canSpeculativelyEmitVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
1904 if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(RD))
1905 return false;
1906
1907 // For a complete-object vtable (or more specifically, for the VTT), we need
1908 // to be able to speculatively emit the vtables of all dynamic virtual bases.
1909 for (const auto &B : RD->vbases()) {
1910 auto *BRD = B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1911 assert(BRD && "no class for base specifier");
1912 if (!BRD->isDynamicClass())
1913 continue;
1914 if (!canSpeculativelyEmitVTableAsBaseClass(BRD))
1915 return false;
1916 }
1917
1918 return true;
1919}
1920static llvm::Value *performTypeAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1921 Address InitialPtr,
1922 int64_t NonVirtualAdjustment,
1923 int64_t VirtualAdjustment,
1924 bool IsReturnAdjustment) {
1925 if (!NonVirtualAdjustment && !VirtualAdjustment)
1926 return InitialPtr.getPointer();
1927
1928 Address V = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(InitialPtr, CGF.Int8Ty);
1929
1930 // In a base-to-derived cast, the non-virtual adjustment is applied first.
1931 if (NonVirtualAdjustment && !IsReturnAdjustment) {
1932 V = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(V,
1933 CharUnits::fromQuantity(NonVirtualAdjustment));
1934 }
1935
1936 // Perform the virtual adjustment if we have one.
1937 llvm::Value *ResultPtr;
1938 if (VirtualAdjustment) {
1939 llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
1940 CGF.ConvertType(CGF.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
1941
1942 Address VTablePtrPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
1943 llvm::Value *VTablePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VTablePtrPtr);
1944
1945 llvm::Value *OffsetPtr =
1946 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(VTablePtr, VirtualAdjustment);
1947
1948 llvm::Value *Offset;
1949 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
1950 OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(OffsetPtr, CGF.Int8PtrPtrTy);
1951 Offset =
1952 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(OffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign(),
1953 "vbase.offset.intcap");
1954 Offset = CGF.getCapabilityIntegerValue(Offset);
1955 } else {
1956 OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(OffsetPtr,
1957 PtrDiffTy->getPointerTo(
1958 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
1959
1960 // Load the adjustment offset from the vtable.
1961 Offset =
1962 CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(OffsetPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
1963 }
1964
1965 // Adjust our pointer.
1966 ResultPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(V.getPointer(), Offset);
1967 } else {
1968 ResultPtr = V.getPointer();
1969 }
1970
1971 // In a derived-to-base conversion, the non-virtual adjustment is
1972 // applied second.
1973 if (NonVirtualAdjustment && IsReturnAdjustment) {
1974 ResultPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(ResultPtr,
1975 NonVirtualAdjustment);
1976 }
1977
1978 // Cast back to the original type.
1979 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ResultPtr, InitialPtr.getType());
1980}
1981
1982llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::performThisAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1983 Address This,
1984 const ThisAdjustment &TA) {
1985 return performTypeAdjustment(CGF, This, TA.NonVirtual,
1986 TA.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset,
1987 /*IsReturnAdjustment=*/false);
1988}
1989
1990llvm::Value *
1991ItaniumCXXABI::performReturnAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Ret,
1992 const ReturnAdjustment &RA) {
1993 return performTypeAdjustment(CGF, Ret, RA.NonVirtual,
1994 RA.Virtual.Itanium.VBaseOffsetOffset,
1995 /*IsReturnAdjustment=*/true);
1996}

1998void ARMCXXABI::EmitReturnFromThunk(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1999 RValue RV, QualType ResultType) {
2000 if (!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl()))
2001 return ItaniumCXXABI::EmitReturnFromThunk(CGF, RV, ResultType);
2002

2007}

2009/************************** Array allocation cookies **************************/
2010
2011CharUnits ItaniumCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(QualType elementType) {
2012 // The array cookie is a size_t; pad that up to the element alignment.
2013 // The cookie is actually right-justified in that space.
2014 return std::max(CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.SizeSizeInBytes),
2015 CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(elementType));
2016}
2017
2018Address ItaniumCXXABI::InitializeArrayCookie(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2019 Address NewPtr,
2020 llvm::Value *NumElements,
2021 const CXXNewExpr *expr,
2022 QualType ElementType) {
2023 assert(requiresArrayCookie(expr));
2024
2025 unsigned AS = NewPtr.getAddressSpace();
2026
2027 ASTContext &Ctx = getContext();
2028 CharUnits SizeSize = CGF.getSizeSize();
2029
2030 // The size of the cookie.
2031 CharUnits CookieSize =
2032 std::max(SizeSize, Ctx.getTypeAlignInChars(ElementType));
2033 assert(CookieSize == getArrayCookieSizeImpl(ElementType));
2034
2035 // Compute an offset to the cookie.
2036 Address CookiePtr = NewPtr;
2037 CharUnits CookieOffset = CookieSize - SizeSize;
2038 if (!CookieOffset.isZero())
2039 CookiePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(CookiePtr, CookieOffset);
2040
2041 // Write the number of elements into the appropriate slot.
2042 Address NumElementsPtr =
2043 CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(CookiePtr, CGF.SizeTy);
2044 llvm::Instruction *SI = CGF.Builder.CreateStore(NumElements, NumElementsPtr);
2045
2046 // Handle the array cookie specially in ASan.
2047 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) && AS == 0 &&
2048 (expr->getOperatorNew()->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction() ||
2049 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeAddressPoisonCustomArrayCookie)) {
2050 // The store to the CookiePtr does not need to be instrumented.
2051 CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForInstruction(SI);
2052 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
2053 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, NumElementsPtr.getType(), false);
2054 llvm::FunctionCallee F =
2055 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__asan_poison_cxx_array_cookie");
2056 CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, NumElementsPtr.getPointer());
2057 }
2058
2059 // Finally, compute a pointer to the actual data buffer by skipping
2060 // over the cookie completely.
2061 return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(NewPtr, CookieSize);
2062}
2063
2064llvm::Value *ItaniumCXXABI::readArrayCookieImpl(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2065 Address allocPtr,
2066 CharUnits cookieSize) {
2067 // The element size is right-justified in the cookie.
2068 Address numElementsPtr = allocPtr;
2069 CharUnits numElementsOffset = cookieSize - CGF.getSizeSize();
2070 if (!numElementsOffset.isZero())
2071 numElementsPtr =
2072 CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(numElementsPtr, numElementsOffset);
2073
2074 unsigned AS = allocPtr.getAddressSpace();
2075 numElementsPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(numElementsPtr, CGF.SizeTy);
2076 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) || AS != 0)
2077 return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(numElementsPtr);
2078 // In asan mode emit a function call instead of a regular load and let the
2079 // run-time deal with it: if the shadow is properly poisoned return the
2080 // cookie, otherwise return 0 to avoid an infinite loop calling DTORs.
2081 // We can't simply ignore this load using nosanitize metadata because
2082 // the metadata may be lost.
2083 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
2084 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.SizeTy, CGF.SizeTy->getPointerTo(0), false);
2085 llvm::FunctionCallee F =
2086 CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FTy, "__asan_load_cxx_array_cookie");
2087 return CGF.Builder.CreateCall(F, numElementsPtr.getPointer());
2088}
2089
2090CharUnits ARMCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(QualType elementType) {
2091 // ARM says that the cookie is always:
2092 // struct array_cookie {
2093 // std::size_t element_size; // element_size != 0
2094 // std::size_t element_count;
2095 // };
2096 // But the base ABI doesn't give anything an alignment greater than
2097 // 8, so we can dismiss this as typical ABI-author blindness to
2098 // actual language complexity and round up to the element alignment.
2099 return std::max(CharUnits::fromQuantity(2 * CGM.SizeSizeInBytes),
2100 CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(elementType));
2101}
2102
2103Address ARMCXXABI::InitializeArrayCookie(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2104 Address newPtr,
2105 llvm::Value *numElements,
2106 const CXXNewExpr *expr,
2107 QualType elementType) {
2108 assert(requiresArrayCookie(expr));
2109
2110 // The cookie is always at the start of the buffer.
2111 Address cookie = newPtr;
2112
2113 // The first element is the element size.
2114 cookie = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(cookie, CGF.SizeTy);
2115 llvm::Value *elementSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy,
2116 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType).getQuantity());
2117 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(elementSize, cookie);
2118
2119 // The second element is the element count.
2120 cookie = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(cookie, 1);
2121 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(numElements, cookie);
2122
2123 // Finally, compute a pointer to the actual data buffer by skipping
2124 // over the cookie completely.
2125 CharUnits cookieSize = ARMCXXABI::getArrayCookieSizeImpl(elementType);
2126 return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(newPtr, cookieSize);
2127}
2128
2129llvm::Value *ARMCXXABI::readArrayCookieImpl(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2130 Address allocPtr,
2131 CharUnits cookieSize) {
2132 // The number of elements is at offset sizeof(size_t) relative to
2133 // the allocated pointer.
2134 Address numElementsPtr
2135 = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(allocPtr, CGF.getSizeSize());
2136
2137 numElementsPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(numElementsPtr, CGF.SizeTy);
2138 return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(numElementsPtr);
2139}
