2192/// The ARM code here follows the Itanium code closely enough that we
2193/// just special-case it at particular places.
2194void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitGuardedInit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2195 const VarDecl &D,
2196 llvm::GlobalVariable *var,
2197 bool shouldPerformInit) {
2198 CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2199
2200 // Inline variables that weren't instantiated from variable templates have
2201 // partially-ordered initialization within their translation unit.
2202 bool NonTemplateInline =
2203 D.isInline() &&
2204 !isTemplateInstantiation(D.getTemplateSpecializationKind());
2205
2206 // We only need to use thread-safe statics for local non-TLS variables and
2207 // inline variables; other global initialization is always single-threaded
2208 // or (through lazy dynamic loading in multiple threads) unsequenced.
2209 bool threadsafe = getContext().getLangOpts().ThreadsafeStatics &&
2210 (D.isLocalVarDecl() || NonTemplateInline) &&
2211 !D.getTLSKind();
2212
2213 // If we have a global variable with internal linkage and thread-safe statics
2214 // are disabled, we can just let the guard variable be of type i8.
2215 bool useInt8GuardVariable = !threadsafe && var->hasInternalLinkage();
2216
2217 llvm::IntegerType *guardTy;
2218 CharUnits guardAlignment;
2219 if (useInt8GuardVariable) {
2220 guardTy = CGF.Int8Ty;
2221 guardAlignment = CharUnits::One();
2222 } else {
2223 // Guard variables are 64 bits in the generic ABI and size width on ARM
2224 // (i.e. 32-bit on AArch32, 64-bit on AArch64).
2225 if (UseARMGuardVarABI) {
2226 guardTy = CGF.SizeTy;
2227 guardAlignment = CGF.getSizeAlign();
2228 } else {
2229 guardTy = CGF.Int64Ty;
2230 guardAlignment = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
2231 CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(guardTy));
2232 }
2233 }
2234 llvm::PointerType *guardPtrTy = guardTy->getPointerTo(
2235 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
2236
2237 // Create the guard variable if we don't already have it (as we
2238 // might if we're double-emitting this function body).
2239 llvm::GlobalVariable *guard = CGM.getStaticLocalDeclGuardAddress(&D);
2240 if (!guard) {
2241 // Mangle the name for the guard.
2242 SmallString<256> guardName;
2243 {
2244 llvm::raw_svector_ostream out(guardName);
2245 getMangleContext().mangleStaticGuardVariable(&D, out);
2246 }
2247
2248 // Create the guard variable with a zero-initializer.
2249 // Just absorb linkage and visibility from the guarded variable.
2250 guard = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), guardTy,
2251 false, var->getLinkage(),
2252 llvm::ConstantInt::get(guardTy, 0),
2253 guardName.str(), nullptr,
2254 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
2255 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
2256 guard->setDSOLocal(var->isDSOLocal());
2257 guard->setVisibility(var->getVisibility());
2258 // If the variable is thread-local, so is its guard variable.
2259 guard->setThreadLocalMode(var->getThreadLocalMode());
2260 guard->setAlignment(guardAlignment.getQuantity());
2261
2262 // The ABI says: "It is suggested that it be emitted in the same COMDAT
2263 // group as the associated data object." In practice, this doesn't work for
2264 // non-ELF and non-Wasm object formats, so only do it for ELF and Wasm.
2265 llvm::Comdat *C = var->getComdat();
2266 if (!D.isLocalVarDecl() && C &&
2267 (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() ||
2268 CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatWasm())) {
2269 guard->setComdat(C);
2270 // An inline variable's guard function is run from the per-TU
2271 // initialization function, not via a dedicated global ctor function, so
2272 // we can't put it in a comdat.
2273 if (!NonTemplateInline)
2274 CGF.CurFn->setComdat(C);
2275 } else if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && guard->isWeakForLinker()) {
2276 guard->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(guard->getName()));
2277 }
2278
2279 CGM.setStaticLocalDeclGuardAddress(&D, guard);
2280 }
2281
2282 Address guardAddr = Address(guard, guardAlignment);
2283
2284 // Test whether the variable has completed initialization.
2285 //
2286 // Itanium C++ ABI 3.3.2:
2287 // The following is pseudo-code showing how these functions can be used:
2288 // if (obj_guard.first_byte == 0) {
2289 // if ( __cxa_guard_acquire (&obj_guard) ) {
2290 // try {
2291 // ... initialize the object ...;
2292 // } catch (...) {
2293 // __cxa_guard_abort (&obj_guard);
2294 // throw;
2295 // }
2296 // ... queue object destructor with __cxa_atexit() ...;
2297 // __cxa_guard_release (&obj_guard);
2298 // }
2299 // }
2300
2301 // Load the first byte of the guard variable.
2302 llvm::LoadInst *LI =
2303 Builder.CreateLoad(Builder.CreateElementBitCast(guardAddr, CGM.Int8Ty));
2304
2305 // Itanium ABI:
2306 // An implementation supporting thread-safety on multiprocessor
2307 // systems must also guarantee that references to the initialized
2308 // object do not occur before the load of the initialization flag.
2309 //
2310 // In LLVM, we do this by marking the load Acquire.
2311 if (threadsafe)
2312 LI->setAtomic(llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire);
2313
2314 // For ARM, we should only check the first bit, rather than the entire byte:
2315 //
2316 // ARM C++ ABI 3.2.3.1:
2317 // To support the potential use of initialization guard variables
2318 // as semaphores that are the target of ARM SWP and LDREX/STREX
2319 // synchronizing instructions we define a static initialization
2320 // guard variable to be a 4-byte aligned, 4-byte word with the
2321 // following inline access protocol.
2322 // #define INITIALIZED 1
2323 // if ((obj_guard & INITIALIZED) != INITIALIZED) {
2324 // if (__cxa_guard_acquire(&obj_guard))
2325 // ...
2326 // }
2327 //
2328 // and similarly for ARM64:
2329 //
2330 // ARM64 C++ ABI 3.2.2:
2331 // This ABI instead only specifies the value bit 0 of the static guard
2332 // variable; all other bits are platform defined. Bit 0 shall be 0 when the
2333 // variable is not initialized and 1 when it is.
2334 llvm::Value *V =
2335 (UseARMGuardVarABI && !useInt8GuardVariable)
2336 ? Builder.CreateAnd(LI, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 1))
2337 : LI;
2338 llvm::Value *NeedsInit = Builder.CreateIsNull(V, "guard.uninitialized");
2339
2340 llvm::BasicBlock *InitCheckBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.check");
2341 llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.end");
2342
2343 // Check if the first byte of the guard variable is zero.
2344 CGF.EmitCXXGuardedInitBranch(NeedsInit, InitCheckBlock, EndBlock,
2345 CodeGenFunction::GuardKind::VariableGuard, &D);
2346
2347 CGF.EmitBlock(InitCheckBlock);
2348
2349 // Variables used when coping with thread-safe statics and exceptions.
2350 if (threadsafe) {
2351 // Call __cxa_guard_acquire.
2352 llvm::Value *V
2353 = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGuardAcquireFn(CGM, guardPtrTy), guard);
2354
2355 llvm::BasicBlock *InitBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init");
2356
2357 Builder.CreateCondBr(Builder.CreateIsNotNull(V, "tobool"),
2358 InitBlock, EndBlock);
2359
2360 // Call __cxa_guard_abort along the exceptional edge.
2361 CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallGuardAbort>(EHCleanup, guard);
2362
2363 CGF.EmitBlock(InitBlock);
2364 }
2365
2366 // Emit the initializer and add a global destructor if appropriate.
2367 CGF.EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInit(D, var, shouldPerformInit);
2368
2369 if (threadsafe) {
2370 // Pop the guard-abort cleanup if we pushed one.
2371 CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
2372
2373 // Call __cxa_guard_release. This cannot throw.
2374 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGuardReleaseFn(CGM, guardPtrTy),
2375 guardAddr.getPointer());
2376 } else {
2377 Builder.CreateStore(llvm::ConstantInt::get(guardTy, 1), guardAddr);
2378 }
2379
2380 CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
2381}
2382
2383/// Register a global destructor using __cxa_atexit.
2384static void emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2385 llvm::FunctionCallee dtor,
2386 llvm::Constant *addr, bool TLS) {
2387 const char *Name = "__cxa_atexit";
2388 if (TLS) {
2389 const llvm::Triple &T = CGF.getTarget().getTriple();
2390 Name = T.isOSDarwin() ? "_tlv_atexit" : "__cxa_thread_atexit";
2391 }
2392
2393 // We're assuming that the destructor function is something we can
2394 // reasonably call with the default CC. Go ahead and cast it to the
2395 // right prototype.
2396 unsigned AS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2397 llvm::Type *dtorTy =
2398 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, CGF.Int8PtrTy, false)->getPointerTo(AS);
2399
2400 // extern "C" int __cxa_atexit(void (*f)(void *), void *p, void *d);
2401 llvm::Type *paramTys[] = { dtorTy, CGF.Int8PtrTy, CGF.Int8PtrTy };
2402 llvm::FunctionType *atexitTy =
2403 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.IntTy, paramTys, false);
2404
2405 // Fetch the actual function.
2406 llvm::FunctionCallee atexit = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(atexitTy, Name);
2407 if (llvm::Function *fn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(atexit.getCallee()))
2408 fn->setDoesNotThrow();
2409
2410 // Create a variable that binds the atexit to this shared object.
2411 llvm::Constant *handle =
2412 CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(CGF.Int8Ty, "__dso_handle", AS);
2413 auto *GV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(handle->stripPointerCasts());
2414 GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
2415
2416 // Convert the destructor pointer to a capability before passing it
2417 llvm::Value *dtorV = dtor.getCallee();
2418 auto &TI = CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo();
2419 if (TI.areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
2420 if (dtorV->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != AS) {
2421 // dtorTy defined above will be the right capability type
2422 dtorV = CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CGF, dtorV, dtorTy);
2423 }
2424 }
2425 dtorV = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(dtorV, dtorTy);
2426
2427 if (!addr)
2428 // addr is null when we are trying to register a dtor annotated with
2429 // __attribute__((destructor)) in a constructor function. Using null here is
2430 // okay because this argument is just passed back to the destructor
2431 // function.
2432 addr = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
2433
2434 // FIXME-cheri-c++: should handle be a capability in the pure ABI?
2435 llvm::Value *args[] = {dtorV,
2436 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(addr, CGF.Int8PtrTy),
2437 handle};
2438 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(atexit, args);
2439}
2440
2441void CodeGenModule::registerGlobalDtorsWithAtExit() {
2442 for (const auto I : DtorsUsingAtExit) {
2443 int Priority = I.first;
2444 const llvm::TinyPtrVector<llvm::Function *> &Dtors = I.second;
2445
2446 // Create a function that registers destructors that have the same priority.
2447 //
2448 // Since constructor functions are run in non-descending order of their
2449 // priorities, destructors are registered in non-descending order of their
2450 // priorities, and since destructor functions are run in the reverse order
2451 // of their registration, destructor functions are run in non-ascending
2452 // order of their priorities.
2453 CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
2454 std::string GlobalInitFnName =
2455 std::string("__GLOBAL_init_") + llvm::to_string(Priority);
2456 llvm::FunctionType *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
2457 llvm::Function *GlobalInitFn = CreateGlobalInitOrDestructFunction(
2458 FTy, GlobalInitFnName, getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(),
2459 SourceLocation());
2460 ASTContext &Ctx = getContext();
2461 QualType ReturnTy = Ctx.VoidTy;
2462 QualType FunctionTy = Ctx.getFunctionType(ReturnTy, llvm::None, {});
2463 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2464 Ctx, Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
2465 &Ctx.Idents.get(GlobalInitFnName), FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static,
2466 false, false);
2467 CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(FD), ReturnTy, GlobalInitFn,
2468 getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(), FunctionArgList(),
2469 SourceLocation(), SourceLocation());
2470
2471 for (auto *Dtor : Dtors) {
2472 // Register the destructor function calling __cxa_atexit if it is
2473 // available. Otherwise fall back on calling atexit.
2474 if (getCodeGenOpts().CXAAtExit)
2475 emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CGF, Dtor, nullptr, false);
2476 else
2477 CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithAtExit(Dtor);
2478 }
2479
2480 CGF.FinishFunction();
2481 AddGlobalCtor(GlobalInitFn, Priority, nullptr);
2482 }
2483}
2484
2485/// Register a global destructor as best as we know how.
2486void ItaniumCXXABI::registerGlobalDtor(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl &D,
2487 llvm::FunctionCallee dtor,
2488 llvm::Constant *addr) {
2489 if (D.isNoDestroy(CGM.getContext()))
2490 return;
2491
2492 // Use __cxa_atexit if available.
2493 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CXAAtExit)
2494 return emitGlobalDtorWithCXAAtExit(CGF, dtor, addr, D.getTLSKind());
2495
2496 if (D.getTLSKind())
2497 CGM.ErrorUnsupported(&D, "non-trivial TLS destruction");
2498
2499 // In Apple kexts, we want to add a global destructor entry.
2500 // FIXME: shouldn't this be guarded by some variable?
2501 if (CGM.getLangOpts().AppleKext) {
2502 // Generate a global destructor entry.
2503 return CGM.AddCXXDtorEntry(dtor, addr);
2504 }
2505
2506 CGF.registerGlobalDtorWithAtExit(D, dtor, addr);
2507}
2508
2509static bool isThreadWrapperReplaceable(const VarDecl *VD,
2510 CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2511 assert(!VD->isStaticLocal() && "static local VarDecls don't need wrappers!");
2512 // Darwin prefers to have references to thread local variables to go through
2513 // the thread wrapper instead of directly referencing the backing variable.
2514 return VD->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
2515 CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin();
2516}
2517
2518/// Get the appropriate linkage for the wrapper function. This is essentially
2519/// the weak form of the variable's linkage; every translation unit which needs
2520/// the wrapper emits a copy, and we want the linker to merge them.
2521static llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
2522getThreadLocalWrapperLinkage(const VarDecl *VD, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2523 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes VarLinkage =
2524 CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, /*isConstant=*/false);
2525
2526 // For internal linkage variables, we don't need an external or weak wrapper.
2527 if (llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(VarLinkage))
2528 return VarLinkage;
2529
2530 // If the thread wrapper is replaceable, give it appropriate linkage.
2531 if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM))
2532 if (!llvm::GlobalVariable::isLinkOnceLinkage(VarLinkage) &&
2533 !llvm::GlobalVariable::isWeakODRLinkage(VarLinkage))
2534 return VarLinkage;
2535 return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
2536}
2537
2538llvm::Function *
2539ItaniumCXXABI::getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(const VarDecl *VD,
2540 llvm::Value *Val) {
2541 // Mangle the name for the thread_local wrapper function.
2542 SmallString<256> WrapperName;
2543 {
2544 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(WrapperName);
2545 getMangleContext().mangleItaniumThreadLocalWrapper(VD, Out);
2546 }
2547
2548 // FIXME: If VD is a definition, we should regenerate the function attributes
2549 // before returning.
2550 if (llvm::Value *V = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(WrapperName))
2551 return cast<llvm::Function>(V);
2552
2553 QualType RetQT = VD->getType();
2554 if (RetQT->isReferenceType())
2555 RetQT = RetQT.getNonReferenceType();
2556
2557 const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(
2558 getContext().getPointerType(RetQT), FunctionArgList());
2559
2560 llvm::FunctionType *FnTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2561 llvm::Function *Wrapper =
2562 llvm::Function::Create(FnTy, getThreadLocalWrapperLinkage(VD, CGM),
2563 WrapperName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
2564
2565 CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, Wrapper);
2566
2567 if (VD->hasDefinition())
2568 CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, Wrapper);
2569
2570 // Always resolve references to the wrapper at link time.
2571 if (!Wrapper->hasLocalLinkage())
2572 if (!isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM) ||
2573 llvm::GlobalVariable::isLinkOnceLinkage(Wrapper->getLinkage()) ||
2574 llvm::GlobalVariable::isWeakODRLinkage(Wrapper->getLinkage()) ||
2575 VD->getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
2576 Wrapper->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
2577
2578 if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM)) {
2579 Wrapper->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2580 Wrapper->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2581 }
2582 return Wrapper;
2583}
2584
2585void ItaniumCXXABI::EmitThreadLocalInitFuncs(
2586 CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocals,
2587 ArrayRef<llvm::Function *> CXXThreadLocalInits,
2588 ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocalInitVars) {
2589 llvm::Function *InitFunc = nullptr;
2590
2591 // Separate initializers into those with ordered (or partially-ordered)
2592 // initialization and those with unordered initialization.
2593 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Function *, 8> OrderedInits;
2594 llvm::SmallDenseMap<const VarDecl *, llvm::Function *> UnorderedInits;
2595 for (unsigned I = 0; I != CXXThreadLocalInits.size(); ++I) {
2596 if (isTemplateInstantiation(
2597 CXXThreadLocalInitVars[I]->getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
2598 UnorderedInits[CXXThreadLocalInitVars[I]->getCanonicalDecl()] =
2599 CXXThreadLocalInits[I];
2600 else
2601 OrderedInits.push_back(CXXThreadLocalInits[I]);
2602 }
2603
2604 if (!OrderedInits.empty()) {
2605 // Generate a guarded initialization function.
2606 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
2607 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);
2608 const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
2609 InitFunc = CGM.CreateGlobalInitOrDestructFunction(FTy, "__tls_init", FI,
2610 SourceLocation(),
2611 /*TLS=*/true);
2612 llvm::GlobalVariable *Guard = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
2613 CGM.getModule(), CGM.Int8Ty, /*isConstant=*/false,
2614 llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage,
2615 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 0), "__tls_guard", nullptr,
2616 // Need to set address space and initially mark as not thread-local
2617 // since that flag is set later.
2618 llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
2619 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTlsAddressSpace());
2620 Guard->setThreadLocal(true);
2621
2622 CharUnits GuardAlign = CharUnits::One();
2623 Guard->setAlignment(GuardAlign.getQuantity());
2624
2625 CodeGenFunction(CGM).GenerateCXXGlobalInitFunc(
2626 InitFunc, OrderedInits, ConstantAddress(Guard, GuardAlign));
2627 // On Darwin platforms, use CXX_FAST_TLS calling convention.
2628 if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
2629 InitFunc->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2630 InitFunc->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2631 }
2632 }
2633
2634 // Emit thread wrappers.
2635 for (const VarDecl *VD : CXXThreadLocals) {
2636 llvm::GlobalVariable *Var =
2637 cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(CGM.GetGlobalValue(CGM.getMangledName(VD)));
2638 llvm::Function *Wrapper = getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(VD, Var);
2639
2640 // Some targets require that all access to thread local variables go through
2641 // the thread wrapper. This means that we cannot attempt to create a thread
2642 // wrapper or a thread helper.
2643 if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM) && !VD->hasDefinition()) {
2644 Wrapper->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
2645 continue;
2646 }
2647
2648 // Mangle the name for the thread_local initialization function.
2649 SmallString<256> InitFnName;
2650 {
2651 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(InitFnName);
2652 getMangleContext().mangleItaniumThreadLocalInit(VD, Out);
2653 }
2654
2655 llvm::FunctionType *InitFnTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, false);
2656
2657 // If we have a definition for the variable, emit the initialization
2658 // function as an alias to the global Init function (if any). Otherwise,
2659 // produce a declaration of the initialization function.
2660 llvm::GlobalValue *Init = nullptr;
2661 bool InitIsInitFunc = false;
2662 if (VD->hasDefinition()) {
2663 InitIsInitFunc = true;
2664 llvm::Function *InitFuncToUse = InitFunc;
2665 if (isTemplateInstantiation(VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()))
2666 InitFuncToUse = UnorderedInits.lookup(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
2667 if (InitFuncToUse)
2668 Init = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Var->getLinkage(), InitFnName.str(),
2669 InitFuncToUse);
2670 } else {
2671 // Emit a weak global function referring to the initialization function.
2672 // This function will not exist if the TU defining the thread_local
2673 // variable in question does not need any dynamic initialization for
2674 // its thread_local variables.
2675 Init = llvm::Function::Create(InitFnTy,
2676 llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalWeakLinkage,
2677 InitFnName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
2678 const CGFunctionInfo &FI = CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction();
2679 CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI,
2680 cast<llvm::Function>(Init));
2681 }
2682
2683 if (Init) {
2684 Init->setVisibility(Var->getVisibility());
2685 Init->setDSOLocal(Var->isDSOLocal());
2686 }
2687
2688 llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getModule().getContext();
2689 llvm::BasicBlock *Entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
2690 CGBuilderTy Builder(CGM, Entry);
2691 if (InitIsInitFunc) {
2692 if (Init) {
2693 llvm::CallInst *CallVal = Builder.CreateCall(InitFnTy, Init);
2694 if (isThreadWrapperReplaceable(VD, CGM)) {
2695 CallVal->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2696 llvm::Function *Fn =
2697 cast<llvm::Function>(cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Init)->getAliasee());
2698 Fn->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::CXX_FAST_TLS);
2699 }
2700 }
2701 } else {
2702 // Don't know whether we have an init function. Call it if it exists.
2703 llvm::Value *Have = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Init);
2704 llvm::BasicBlock *InitBB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
2705 llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", Wrapper);
2706 Builder.CreateCondBr(Have, InitBB, ExitBB);
2707
2708 Builder.SetInsertPoint(InitBB);
2709 Builder.CreateCall(InitFnTy, Init);
2710 Builder.CreateBr(ExitBB);
2711
2712 Builder.SetInsertPoint(ExitBB);
2713 }
2714
2715 // For a reference, the result of the wrapper function is a pointer to
2716 // the referenced object.
2717 llvm::Value *Val = Var;
2718 if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
2719 CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
2720 Val = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Val, Align);
2721 }
2722 if (Val->getType() != Wrapper->getReturnType())
2723 Val = Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2724 Val, Wrapper->getReturnType(), "");
2725 Builder.CreateRet(Val);
2726 }
2727}
2728
2729LValue ItaniumCXXABI::EmitThreadLocalVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2730 const VarDecl *VD,
2731 QualType LValType) {
2732 llvm::Value *Val = CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
2733 llvm::Function *Wrapper = getOrCreateThreadLocalWrapper(VD, Val);
2734
2735 llvm::CallInst *CallVal = CGF.Builder.CreateCall(Wrapper);
2736 CallVal->setCallingConv(Wrapper->getCallingConv());
2737
2738 LValue LV;
2739 if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
2740 LV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(CallVal, LValType);
2741 else
2742 LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(CallVal, LValType,
2743 CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
2744 // FIXME: need setObjCGCLValueClass?
2745 return LV;
2746}
2747
2748/// Return whether the given global decl needs a VTT parameter, which it does
2749/// if it's a base constructor or destructor with virtual bases.
2750bool ItaniumCXXABI::NeedsVTTParameter(GlobalDecl GD) {
2751 const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2752
2753 // We don't have any virtual bases, just return early.
2754 if (!MD->getParent()->getNumVBases())
2755 return false;
2756
2757 // Check if we have a base constructor.
2758 if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Base)
2759 return true;
2760
2761 // Check if we have a base destructor.
2762 if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) && GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base)
2763 return true;
2764
2765 return false;
2766}

2869llvm::GlobalVariable *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::GetAddrOfTypeName(
2870 QualType Ty, llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage) {
2871 SmallString<256> Name;
2872 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
2873 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIName(Ty, Out);
2874
2875 // We know that the mangled name of the type starts at index 4 of the
2876 // mangled name of the typename, so we can just index into it in order to
2877 // get the mangled name of the type.
2878 llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext,
2879 Name.substr(4));

2890llvm::Constant *

2893 SmallString<256> Name;
2894 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
2895 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
2896
2897 // Look for an existing global.
2898 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
2899
2900 if (!GV) {
2901 // Create a new global variable.
2902 // Note for the future: If we would ever like to do deferred emission of
2903 // RTTI, check if emitting vtables opportunistically need any adjustment.
2904
2905 GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), CGM.Int8PtrTy,
2906 /*Constant=*/true,
2907 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
2908 Name, nullptr,
2909 llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
2910 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
2911 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2912 CGM.setGVProperties(GV, RD);
2913 }
2914
2915 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
2916}

2918/// TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary - Given a builtin type, returns whether the type
2919/// info for that type is defined in the standard library.
2920static bool TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(const BuiltinType *Ty) {
2921 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.2:
2922 // Basic type information (e.g. for "int", "bool", etc.) will be kept in
2923 // the run-time support library. Specifically, the run-time support
2924 // library should contain type_info objects for the types X, X* and
2925 // X const*, for every X in: void, std::nullptr_t, bool, wchar_t, char,
2926 // unsigned char, signed char, short, unsigned short, int, unsigned int,
2927 // long, unsigned long, long long, unsigned long long, float, double,
2928 // long double, char16_t, char32_t, and the IEEE 754r decimal and
2929 // half-precision floating point types.
2930 //
2931 // GCC also emits RTTI for __int128.
2932 // FIXME: We do not emit RTTI information for decimal types here.
2933
2934 // Types added here must also be added to EmitFundamentalRTTIDescriptors.
2935 switch (Ty->getKind()) {
2936 case BuiltinType::Void:
2937 case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
2938 case BuiltinType::Bool:
2939 case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
2940 case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
2941 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
2942 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
2943 case BuiltinType::UChar:
2944 case BuiltinType::SChar:
2945 case BuiltinType::Short:
2946 case BuiltinType::UShort:
2947 case BuiltinType::Int:
2948 case BuiltinType::UInt:
2949 case BuiltinType::Long:
2950 case BuiltinType::ULong:
2951 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
2952 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
2953 case BuiltinType::Half:
2954 case BuiltinType::Float:
2955 case BuiltinType::Double:
2956 case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
2957 case BuiltinType::Float16:
2958 case BuiltinType::Float128:
2959 case BuiltinType::Char8:
2960 case BuiltinType::Char16:
2961 case BuiltinType::Char32:
2962 case BuiltinType::Int128:
2963 case BuiltinType::UInt128:
2964 return true;
2965
2966#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
2967 case BuiltinType::Id:
2968#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
2969#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
2970 case BuiltinType::Id:
2971#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
2972 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
2973 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
2974 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
2975 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
2976 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
2977 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
2978 case BuiltinType::Accum:
2979 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
2980 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
2981 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
2982 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
2983 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
2984 case BuiltinType::Fract:
2985 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
2986 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
2987 case BuiltinType::UFract:
2988 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
2989 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
2990 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
2991 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
2992 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
2993 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
2994 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
2995 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
2996 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
2997 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
2998 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
2999 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
3000 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
3001 return false;
3002
3003 case BuiltinType::Dependent:
3004#define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId)
3005#define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) \
3006 case BuiltinType::Id:
3007#include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
3008 llvm_unreachable("asking for RRTI for a placeholder type!");
3009
3010 case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
3011 case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
3012 case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
3013 llvm_unreachable("FIXME: Objective-C types are unsupported!");
3014 case BuiltinType::UIntCap:
3015 case BuiltinType::IntCap:
3016 llvm_unreachable("Capability types not supported in RTTI yet!");
3017 }
3018
3019 llvm_unreachable("Invalid BuiltinType Kind!");
3020}

3022static bool TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(const PointerType *PointerTy) {
3023 QualType PointeeTy = PointerTy->getPointeeType();
3024 const BuiltinType *BuiltinTy = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(PointeeTy);
3025 if (!BuiltinTy)
3026 return false;
3027
3028 // Check the qualifiers.
3029 Qualifiers Quals = PointeeTy.getQualifiers();
3030 Quals.removeConst();
3031
3032 if (!Quals.empty())
3033 return false;
3034
3035 return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(BuiltinTy);
3036}
3037
3038/// IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor - Returns whether the type
3039/// information for the given type exists in the standard library.
3040static bool IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty) {
3041 // Type info for builtin types is defined in the standard library.
3042 if (const BuiltinType *BuiltinTy = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(Ty))
3043 return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(BuiltinTy);
3044
3045 // Type info for some pointer types to builtin types is defined in the
3046 // standard library.
3047 if (const PointerType *PointerTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty))
3048 return TypeInfoIsInStandardLibrary(PointerTy);
3049
3050 return false;
3051}
3052
3053/// ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor - Returns whether the type information for
3054/// the given type exists somewhere else, and that we should not emit the type
3055/// information in this translation unit. Assumes that it is not a
3056/// standard-library type.
3057static bool ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3058 QualType Ty) {
3059 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
3060
3061 // If RTTI is disabled, assume it might be disabled in the
3062 // translation unit that defines any potential key function, too.
3063 if (!Context.getLangOpts().RTTI) return false;
3064
3065 if (const RecordType *RecordTy = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3066 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordTy->getDecl());
3067 if (!RD->hasDefinition())
3068 return false;
3069
3070 if (!RD->isDynamicClass())
3071 return false;
3072
3073 // FIXME: this may need to be reconsidered if the key function
3074 // changes.
3075 // N.B. We must always emit the RTTI data ourselves if there exists a key
3076 // function.
3077 bool IsDLLImport = RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
3078
3079 // Don't import the RTTI but emit it locally.
3080 if (CGM.getTriple().isWindowsGNUEnvironment())
3081 return false;
3082
3083 if (CGM.getVTables().isVTableExternal(RD))
3084 return IsDLLImport && !CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment()
3085 ? false
3086 : true;
3087
3088 if (IsDLLImport)
3089 return true;
3090 }
3091
3092 return false;
3093}

3095/// IsIncompleteClassType - Returns whether the given record type is incomplete.
3096static bool IsIncompleteClassType(const RecordType *RecordTy) {
3097 return !RecordTy->getDecl()->isCompleteDefinition();
3098}
3099
3100/// ContainsIncompleteClassType - Returns whether the given type contains an
3101/// incomplete class type. This is true if
3102///
3103/// * The given type is an incomplete class type.
3104/// * The given type is a pointer type whose pointee type contains an
3105/// incomplete class type.
3106/// * The given type is a member pointer type whose class is an incomplete
3107/// class type.
3108/// * The given type is a member pointer type whoise pointee type contains an
3109/// incomplete class type.
3110/// is an indirect or direct pointer to an incomplete class type.
3111static bool ContainsIncompleteClassType(QualType Ty) {
3112 if (const RecordType *RecordTy = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3113 if (IsIncompleteClassType(RecordTy))
3114 return true;
3115 }
3116
3117 if (const PointerType *PointerTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty))
3118 return ContainsIncompleteClassType(PointerTy->getPointeeType());
3119
3120 if (const MemberPointerType *MemberPointerTy =
3121 dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty)) {
3122 // Check if the class type is incomplete.
3123 const RecordType *ClassType = cast<RecordType>(MemberPointerTy->getClass());
3124 if (IsIncompleteClassType(ClassType))
3125 return true;
3126
3127 return ContainsIncompleteClassType(MemberPointerTy->getPointeeType());
3128 }
3129
3130 return false;
3131}
3132
3133// CanUseSingleInheritance - Return whether the given record decl has a "single,
3134// public, non-virtual base at offset zero (i.e. the derived class is dynamic
3135// iff the base is)", according to Itanium C++ ABI, 2.95p6b.
3136static bool CanUseSingleInheritance(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3137 // Check the number of bases.
3138 if (RD->getNumBases() != 1)
3139 return false;
3140
3141 // Get the base.
3142 CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_iterator Base = RD->bases_begin();
3143
3144 // Check that the base is not virtual.
3145 if (Base->isVirtual())
3146 return false;
3147
3148 // Check that the base is public.
3149 if (Base->getAccessSpecifier() != AS_public)
3150 return false;
3151
3152 // Check that the class is dynamic iff the base is.
3153 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl =
3154 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
3155 if (!BaseDecl->isEmpty() &&
3156 BaseDecl->isDynamicClass() != RD->isDynamicClass())
3157 return false;
3158
3159 return true;
3160}
3161
3162void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildVTablePointer(const Type *Ty) {
3163 // abi::__class_type_info.
3164 static const char * const ClassTypeInfo =
3165 "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv117__class_type_infoE";
3166 // abi::__si_class_type_info.
3167 static const char * const SIClassTypeInfo =
3168 "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv120__si_class_type_infoE";
3169 // abi::__vmi_class_type_info.
3170 static const char * const VMIClassTypeInfo =
3171 "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv121__vmi_class_type_infoE";
3172
3173 const char *VTableName = nullptr;
3174
3175 switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
3176#define TYPE(Class, Base)
3177#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3178#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3179#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3180#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3181#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3182 llvm_unreachable("Non-canonical and dependent types shouldn't get here");
3183
3184 case Type::LValueReference:
3185 case Type::RValueReference:
3186 llvm_unreachable("References shouldn't get here");
3187
3188 case Type::Auto:
3189 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3190 llvm_unreachable("Undeduced type shouldn't get here");
3191
3192 case Type::Pipe:
3193 llvm_unreachable("Pipe types shouldn't get here");
3194
3195 case Type::Builtin:
3196 // GCC treats vector and complex types as fundamental types.
3197 case Type::Vector:
3198 case Type::ExtVector:
3199 case Type::Complex:
3200 case Type::Atomic:
3201 // FIXME: GCC treats block pointers as fundamental types?!
3202 case Type::BlockPointer:
3203 // abi::__fundamental_type_info.
3204 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv123__fundamental_type_infoE";
3205 break;
3206
3207 case Type::ConstantArray:
3208 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3209 case Type::VariableArray:
3210 // abi::__array_type_info.
3211 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv117__array_type_infoE";
3212 break;
3213
3214 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3215 case Type::FunctionProto:
3216 // abi::__function_type_info.
3217 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv120__function_type_infoE";
3218 break;
3219
3220 case Type::Enum:
3221 // abi::__enum_type_info.
3222 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv116__enum_type_infoE";
3223 break;
3224
3225 case Type::Record: {
3226 const CXXRecordDecl *RD =
3227 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(cast<RecordType>(Ty)->getDecl());
3228
3229 if (!RD->hasDefinition() || !RD->getNumBases()) {
3230 VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3231 } else if (CanUseSingleInheritance(RD)) {
3232 VTableName = SIClassTypeInfo;
3233 } else {
3234 VTableName = VMIClassTypeInfo;
3235 }
3236
3237 break;
3238 }
3239
3240 case Type::ObjCObject:
3241 // Ignore protocol qualifiers.
3242 Ty = cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty)->getBaseType().getTypePtr();
3243
3244 // Handle id and Class.
3245 if (isa<BuiltinType>(Ty)) {
3246 VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3247 break;
3248 }
3249
3250 assert(isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty));
3251 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3252
3253 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3254 if (cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty)->getDecl()->getSuperClass()) {
3255 VTableName = SIClassTypeInfo;
3256 } else {
3257 VTableName = ClassTypeInfo;
3258 }
3259 break;
3260
3261 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3262 case Type::Pointer:
3263 // abi::__pointer_type_info.
3264 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv119__pointer_type_infoE";
3265 break;
3266
3267 case Type::MemberPointer:
3268 // abi::__pointer_to_member_type_info.
3269 VTableName = "_ZTVN10__cxxabiv129__pointer_to_member_type_infoE";
3270 break;
3271 }
3272
3273 llvm::Constant *VTable =
3274 CGM.getModule().getGlobalVariable(VTableName);
3275 if (VTable)
3276 VTable = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(VTable, CGM.Int8PtrPtrTy);
3277 else {
3278 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
3279 VTable = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), CGM.Int8PtrTy, /*isConstant*/true,
3280 llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage, nullptr, VTableName,
3281 nullptr, llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal, DefaultAS);
3282 }
3283 CGM.setDSOLocal(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(VTable->stripPointerCasts()));
3284
3285 llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
3286 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().getPointerDiffType());
3287
3288 // The vtable address point is 2.
3289 llvm::Constant *Two = llvm::ConstantInt::get(PtrDiffTy, 2);
3290 VTable =
3291 llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(CGM.Int8PtrTy, VTable, Two);
3292 VTable = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(VTable, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3293
3294 Fields.push_back(VTable);
3295}

3297/// Return the linkage that the type info and type info name constants
3298/// should have for the given type.
3299static llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes getTypeInfoLinkage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3300 QualType Ty) {
3301 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3302 // In addition, it and all of the intermediate abi::__pointer_type_info
3303 // structs in the chain down to the abi::__class_type_info for the
3304 // incomplete class type must be prevented from resolving to the
3305 // corresponding type_info structs for the complete class type, possibly
3306 // by making them local static objects. Finally, a dummy class RTTI is
3307 // generated for the incomplete type that will not resolve to the final
3308 // complete class RTTI (because the latter need not exist), possibly by
3309 // making it a local static object.
3310 if (ContainsIncompleteClassType(Ty))
3311 return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3312
3313 switch (Ty->getLinkage()) {
3314 case NoLinkage:
3315 case InternalLinkage:
3316 case UniqueExternalLinkage:
3317 return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3318
3319 case VisibleNoLinkage:
3320 case ModuleInternalLinkage:
3321 case ModuleLinkage:
3322 case ExternalLinkage:
3323 // RTTI is not enabled, which means that this type info struct is going
3324 // to be used for exception handling. Give it linkonce_odr linkage.
3325 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().RTTI)
3326 return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
3327
3328 if (const RecordType *Record = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Ty)) {
3329 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl());
3330 if (RD->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
3331 return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
3332 if (CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment())
3333 if (RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() &&
3334 ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CGM, Ty))
3335 return llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage;
3336 // MinGW always uses LinkOnceODRLinkage for type info.
3337 if (RD->isDynamicClass() &&
3338 !CGM.getContext()
3339 .getTargetInfo()
3340 .getTriple()
3341 .isWindowsGNUEnvironment())
3342 return CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
3343 }
3344
3345 return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
3346 }
3347
3348 llvm_unreachable("Invalid linkage!");
3349}
3350
3351llvm::Constant *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildTypeInfo(QualType Ty) {
3352 // We want to operate on the canonical type.
3353 Ty = Ty.getCanonicalType();
3354
3355 // Check if we've already emitted an RTTI descriptor for this type.
3356 SmallString<256> Name;
3357 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3358 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
3359
3360 llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
3361 if (OldGV && !OldGV->isDeclaration()) {
3362 assert(!OldGV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage() &&
3363 "available_externally typeinfos not yet implemented");
3364
3365 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(OldGV, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3366 }
3367
3368 // Check if there is already an external RTTI descriptor for this type.
3369 if (IsStandardLibraryRTTIDescriptor(Ty) ||
3370 ShouldUseExternalRTTIDescriptor(CGM, Ty))
3371 return GetAddrOfExternalRTTIDescriptor(Ty);
3372
3373 // Emit the standard library with external linkage.
3374 llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage = getTypeInfoLinkage(CGM, Ty);
3375
3376 // Give the type_info object and name the formal visibility of the
3377 // type itself.
3378 llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes llvmVisibility;
3379 if (llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage))
3380 // If the linkage is local, only default visibility makes sense.
3381 llvmVisibility = llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility;
3382 else if (CXXABI.classifyRTTIUniqueness(Ty, Linkage) ==
3383 ItaniumCXXABI::RUK_NonUniqueHidden)
3384 llvmVisibility = llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility;
3385 else
3386 llvmVisibility = CodeGenModule::GetLLVMVisibility(Ty->getVisibility());
3387
3388 llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes DLLStorageClass =
3389 llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass;
3390 if (CGM.getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment()) {
3391 auto RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3392 if (RD && RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
3393 DLLStorageClass = llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass;
3394 }
3395
3396 return BuildTypeInfo(Ty, Linkage, llvmVisibility, DLLStorageClass);
3397}
3398
3399llvm::Constant *ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildTypeInfo(
3400 QualType Ty,
3401 llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage,
3402 llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes Visibility,
3403 llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes DLLStorageClass) {
3404 // Add the vtable pointer.
3405 BuildVTablePointer(cast<Type>(Ty));
3406
3407 // And the name.
3408 llvm::GlobalVariable *TypeName = GetAddrOfTypeName(Ty, Linkage);
3409 llvm::Constant *TypeNameField;
3410
3411 // If we're supposed to demote the visibility, be sure to set a flag
3412 // to use a string comparison for type_info comparisons.
3413 ItaniumCXXABI::RTTIUniquenessKind RTTIUniqueness =
3414 CXXABI.classifyRTTIUniqueness(Ty, Linkage);
3415 if (RTTIUniqueness != ItaniumCXXABI::RUK_Unique) {
3416 // The flag is the sign bit, which on ARM64 is defined to be clear
3417 // for global pointers. This is very ARM64-specific.
3418 TypeNameField = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(TypeName, CGM.Int64Ty);
3419 llvm::Constant *flag =
3420 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int64Ty, ((uint64_t)1) << 63);
3421 TypeNameField = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAdd(TypeNameField, flag);
3422 TypeNameField =
3423 llvm::ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(TypeNameField, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3424 } else {
3425 TypeNameField = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(TypeName, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3426 }
3427 Fields.push_back(TypeNameField);
3428
3429 switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
3430#define TYPE(Class, Base)
3431#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3432#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3433#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3434#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3435#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3436 llvm_unreachable("Non-canonical and dependent types shouldn't get here");
3437
3438 // GCC treats vector types as fundamental types.
3439 case Type::Builtin:
3440 case Type::Vector:
3441 case Type::ExtVector:
3442 case Type::Complex:
3443 case Type::BlockPointer:
3444 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p4:
3445 // abi::__fundamental_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3446 break;
3447
3448 case Type::LValueReference:
3449 case Type::RValueReference:
3450 llvm_unreachable("References shouldn't get here");
3451
3452 case Type::Auto:
3453 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3454 llvm_unreachable("Undeduced type shouldn't get here");
3455
3456 case Type::Pipe:
3457 llvm_unreachable("Pipe type shouldn't get here");
3458
3459 case Type::ConstantArray:
3460 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3461 case Type::VariableArray:
3462 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3463 // abi::__array_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3464 break;
3465
3466 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3467 case Type::FunctionProto:
3468 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3469 // abi::__function_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3470 break;
3471
3472 case Type::Enum:
3473 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p5:
3474 // abi::__enum_type_info adds no data members to std::type_info.
3475 break;
3476
3477 case Type::Record: {
3478 const CXXRecordDecl *RD =
3479 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(cast<RecordType>(Ty)->getDecl());
3480 if (!RD->hasDefinition() || !RD->getNumBases()) {
3481 // We don't need to emit any fields.
3482 break;
3483 }
3484
3485 if (CanUseSingleInheritance(RD))
3486 BuildSIClassTypeInfo(RD);
3487 else
3488 BuildVMIClassTypeInfo(RD);
3489
3490 break;
3491 }
3492
3493 case Type::ObjCObject:
3494 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3495 BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty));
3496 break;
3497
3498 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3499 BuildPointerTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType());
3500 break;
3501
3502 case Type::Pointer:
3503 BuildPointerTypeInfo(cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType());
3504 break;
3505
3506 case Type::MemberPointer:
3507 BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo(cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty));
3508 break;
3509
3510 case Type::Atomic:
3511 // No fields, at least for the moment.
3512 break;
3513 }
3514
3515 llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
3516
3517 SmallString<256> Name;
3518 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
3519 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty, Out);
3520 llvm::Module &M = CGM.getModule();
3521 llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = M.getNamedGlobal(Name);
3522 llvm::GlobalVariable *GV =
3523 new llvm::GlobalVariable(M, Init->getType(),
3524 /*Constant=*/true, Linkage, Init, Name,
3525 nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
3526 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
3527
3528 // If there's already an old global variable, replace it with the new one.
3529 if (OldGV) {
3530 GV->takeName(OldGV);
3531 llvm::Constant *NewPtr =
3532 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, OldGV->getType());
3533 OldGV->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPtr);
3534 OldGV->eraseFromParent();
3535 }
3536
3537 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker())
3538 GV->setComdat(M.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3539
3540 CharUnits Align =
3541 CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(0));
3542 GV->setAlignment(Align.getQuantity());
3543
3544 // The Itanium ABI specifies that type_info objects must be globally
3545 // unique, with one exception: if the type is an incomplete class
3546 // type or a (possibly indirect) pointer to one. That exception
3547 // affects the general case of comparing type_info objects produced
3548 // by the typeid operator, which is why the comparison operators on
3549 // std::type_info generally use the type_info name pointers instead
3550 // of the object addresses. However, the language's built-in uses
3551 // of RTTI generally require class types to be complete, even when
3552 // manipulating pointers to those class types. This allows the
3553 // implementation of dynamic_cast to rely on address equality tests,
3554 // which is much faster.
3555
3556 // All of this is to say that it's important that both the type_info
3557 // object and the type_info name be uniqued when weakly emitted.
3558
3559 TypeName->setVisibility(Visibility);
3560 CGM.setDSOLocal(TypeName);
3561
3562 GV->setVisibility(Visibility);
3563 CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
3564
3565 TypeName->setDLLStorageClass(DLLStorageClass);
3566 GV->setDLLStorageClass(DLLStorageClass);
3567
3568 TypeName->setPartition(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SymbolPartition);
3569 GV->setPartition(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SymbolPartition);
3570
3571 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, CGM.Int8PtrTy);
3572}

3574/// BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo - Build the appropriate kind of type_info
3575/// for the given Objective-C object type.
3576void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildObjCObjectTypeInfo(const ObjCObjectType *OT) {
3577 // Drop qualifiers.
3578 const Type *T = OT->getBaseType().getTypePtr();
3579 assert(isa<BuiltinType>(T) || isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(T));
3580
3581 // The builtin types are abi::__class_type_infos and don't require
3582 // extra fields.
3583 if (isa<BuiltinType>(T)) return;
3584
3585 ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T)->getDecl();
3586 ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = Class->getSuperClass();
3587
3588 // Root classes are also __class_type_info.
3589 if (!Super) return;
3590
3591 QualType SuperTy = CGM.getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(Super);
3592
3593 // Everything else is single inheritance.
3594 llvm::Constant *BaseTypeInfo =
3595 ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(SuperTy);
3596 Fields.push_back(BaseTypeInfo);
3597}

3605 llvm::Constant *BaseTypeInfo =

3610namespace {
3611 /// SeenBases - Contains virtual and non-virtual bases seen when traversing
3612 /// a class hierarchy.
3613 struct SeenBases {
3614 llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 16> NonVirtualBases;
3615 llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 16> VirtualBases;
3616 };
3617}
3618
3619/// ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags - Compute the value of the flags member in
3620/// abi::__vmi_class_type_info.
3621///
3622static unsigned ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(const CXXBaseSpecifier *Base,
3623 SeenBases &Bases) {
3624
3625 unsigned Flags = 0;
3626
3627 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl =
3628 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
3629
3630 if (Base->isVirtual()) {
3631 // Mark the virtual base as seen.
3632 if (!Bases.VirtualBases.insert(BaseDecl).second) {
3633 // If this virtual base has been seen before, then the class is diamond
3634 // shaped.
3635 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_DiamondShaped;
3636 } else {
3637 if (Bases.NonVirtualBases.count(BaseDecl))
3638 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
3639 }
3640 } else {
3641 // Mark the non-virtual base as seen.
3642 if (!Bases.NonVirtualBases.insert(BaseDecl).second) {
3643 // If this non-virtual base has been seen before, then the class has non-
3644 // diamond shaped repeated inheritance.
3645 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
3646 } else {
3647 if (Bases.VirtualBases.count(BaseDecl))
3648 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::VMI_NonDiamondRepeat;
3649 }
3650 }
3651
3652 // Walk all bases.
3653 for (const auto &I : BaseDecl->bases())
3654 Flags |= ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(&I, Bases);
3655
3656 return Flags;
3657}
3658
3659static unsigned ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3660 unsigned Flags = 0;
3661 SeenBases Bases;
3662
3663 // Walk all bases.
3664 for (const auto &I : RD->bases())
3665 Flags |= ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(&I, Bases);
3666
3667 return Flags;
3668}
3669
3670/// BuildVMIClassTypeInfo - Build an abi::__vmi_class_type_info, used for
3671/// classes with bases that do not satisfy the abi::__si_class_type_info
3672/// constraints, according ti the Itanium C++ ABI, 2.9.5p5c.
3673void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildVMIClassTypeInfo(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3674 llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
3675 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
3676
3677 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
3678 // __flags is a word with flags describing details about the class
3679 // structure, which may be referenced by using the __flags_masks
3680 // enumeration. These flags refer to both direct and indirect bases.
3681 unsigned Flags = ComputeVMIClassTypeInfoFlags(RD);
3682 Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
3683
3684 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
3685 // __base_count is a word with the number of direct proper base class
3686 // descriptions that follow.
3687 Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, RD->getNumBases()));
3688
3689 if (!RD->getNumBases())
3690 return;
3691
3692 // Now add the base class descriptions.
3693
3694 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p6c:
3695 // __base_info[] is an array of base class descriptions -- one for every
3696 // direct proper base. Each description is of the type:
3697 //
3698 // struct abi::__base_class_type_info {
3699 // public:
3700 // const __class_type_info *__base_type;
3701 // long __offset_flags;
3702 //
3703 // enum __offset_flags_masks {
3704 // __virtual_mask = 0x1,
3705 // __public_mask = 0x2,
3706 // __offset_shift = 8
3707 // };
3708 // };
3709
3710 // If we're in mingw and 'long' isn't wide enough for a pointer, use 'long
3711 // long' instead of 'long' for __offset_flags. libstdc++abi uses long long on
3712 // LLP64 platforms.
3713 // FIXME: Consider updating libc++abi to match, and extend this logic to all
3714 // LLP64 platforms.
3715 QualType OffsetFlagsTy = CGM.getContext().LongTy;
3716 const TargetInfo &TI = CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo();
3717 if (TI.getTriple().isOSCygMing() && TI.getPointerWidth(0) > TI.getLongWidth())
3718 OffsetFlagsTy = CGM.getContext().LongLongTy;
3719 llvm::Type *OffsetFlagsLTy =
3720 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(OffsetFlagsTy);
3721
3722 for (const auto &Base : RD->bases()) {
3723 // The __base_type member points to the RTTI for the base type.
3724 Fields.push_back(ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(Base.getType()));
3725
3726 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl =
3727 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
3728
3729 int64_t OffsetFlags = 0;
3730
3731 // All but the lower 8 bits of __offset_flags are a signed offset.
3732 // For a non-virtual base, this is the offset in the object of the base
3733 // subobject. For a virtual base, this is the offset in the virtual table of
3734 // the virtual base offset for the virtual base referenced (negative).
3735 CharUnits Offset;
3736 if (Base.isVirtual())
3737 Offset =
3738 CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(RD, BaseDecl);
3739 else {
3740 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3741 Offset = Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
3742 };
3743
3744 OffsetFlags = uint64_t(Offset.getQuantity()) << 8;
3745
3746 // The low-order byte of __offset_flags contains flags, as given by the
3747 // masks from the enumeration __offset_flags_masks.
3748 if (Base.isVirtual())
3749 OffsetFlags |= BCTI_Virtual;
3750 if (Base.getAccessSpecifier() == AS_public)
3751 OffsetFlags |= BCTI_Public;
3752
3753 Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(OffsetFlagsLTy, OffsetFlags));
3754 }
3755}
3756
3757/// Compute the flags for a __pbase_type_info, and remove the corresponding
3758/// pieces from \p Type.
3759static unsigned extractPBaseFlags(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType &Type) {
3760 unsigned Flags = 0;
3761
3762 if (Type.isConstQualified())
3763 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Const;
3764 if (Type.isVolatileQualified())
3765 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Volatile;
3766 if (Type.isRestrictQualified())
3767 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Restrict;
3768 Type = Type.getUnqualifiedType();
3769
3770 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3771 // When the abi::__pbase_type_info is for a direct or indirect pointer to an
3772 // incomplete class type, the incomplete target type flag is set.
3773 if (ContainsIncompleteClassType(Type))
3774 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Incomplete;
3775
3776 if (auto *Proto = Type->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
3777 if (Proto->isNothrow()) {
3778 Flags |= ItaniumRTTIBuilder::PTI_Noexcept;
3779 Type = Ctx.getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(Type, EST_None);
3780 }
3781 }
3782
3783 return Flags;
3784}

3786/// BuildPointerTypeInfo - Build an abi::__pointer_type_info struct,
3787/// used for pointer types.
3788void ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildPointerTypeInfo(QualType PointeeTy) {
3789 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3790 // __flags is a flag word describing the cv-qualification and other
3791 // attributes of the type pointed to
3792 unsigned Flags = extractPBaseFlags(CGM.getContext(), PointeeTy);
3793
3794 llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
3795 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
3796 Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
3797
3798 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3799 // __pointee is a pointer to the std::type_info derivation for the
3800 // unqualified type being pointed to.
3801 llvm::Constant *PointeeTypeInfo =
3802 ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(PointeeTy);
3803 Fields.push_back(PointeeTypeInfo);
3804}

3806/// BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo - Build an abi::__pointer_to_member_type_info
3807/// struct, used for member pointer types.
3808void
3809ItaniumRTTIBuilder::BuildPointerToMemberTypeInfo(const MemberPointerType *Ty) {
3810 QualType PointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
3811
3812 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3813 // __flags is a flag word describing the cv-qualification and other
3814 // attributes of the type pointed to.
3815 unsigned Flags = extractPBaseFlags(CGM.getContext(), PointeeTy);
3816
3817 const RecordType *ClassType = cast<RecordType>(Ty->getClass());
3818 if (IsIncompleteClassType(ClassType))
3819 Flags |= PTI_ContainingClassIncomplete;
3820
3821 llvm::Type *UnsignedIntLTy =
3822 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(CGM.getContext().UnsignedIntTy);
3823 Fields.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(UnsignedIntLTy, Flags));
3824
3825 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p7:
3826 // __pointee is a pointer to the std::type_info derivation for the
3827 // unqualified type being pointed to.
3828 llvm::Constant *PointeeTypeInfo =
3829 ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(PointeeTy);
3830 Fields.push_back(PointeeTypeInfo);
3831
3832 // Itanium C++ ABI 2.9.5p9:
3833 // __context is a pointer to an abi::__class_type_info corresponding to the
3834 // class type containing the member pointed to
3835 // (e.g., the "A" in "int A::*").
3836 Fields.push_back(
3837 ItaniumRTTIBuilder(CXXABI).BuildTypeInfo(QualType(ClassType, 0)));
3838}

3878/// What sort of uniqueness rules should we use for the RTTI for the
3879/// given type?
3880ItaniumCXXABI::RTTIUniquenessKind ItaniumCXXABI::classifyRTTIUniqueness(
3881 QualType CanTy, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage) const {
3882 if (shouldRTTIBeUnique())
3883 return RUK_Unique;
3884
3885 // It's only necessary for linkonce_odr or weak_odr linkage.
3886 if (Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage &&
3887 Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage)
3888 return RUK_Unique;
3889
3890 // It's only necessary with default visibility.
3891 if (CanTy->getVisibility() != DefaultVisibility)
3892 return RUK_Unique;
3893
3894 // If we're not required to publish this symbol, hide it.
3895 if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage)
3896 return RUK_NonUniqueHidden;
3897
3898 // If we're required to publish this symbol, as we might be under an
3899 // explicit instantiation, leave it with default visibility but
3900 // enable string-comparisons.
3901 assert(Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage);
3902 return RUK_NonUniqueVisible;
3903}

3905// Find out how to codegen the complete destructor and constructor
3906namespace {
3907enum class StructorCodegen { Emit, RAUW, Alias, COMDAT };
3908}
3909static StructorCodegen getCodegenToUse(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3910 const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
3911 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().CXXCtorDtorAliases)
3912 return StructorCodegen::Emit;
3913
3914 // The complete and base structors are not equivalent if there are any virtual
3915 // bases, so emit separate functions.
3916 if (MD->getParent()->getNumVBases())
3917 return StructorCodegen::Emit;
3918
3919 GlobalDecl AliasDecl;
3920 if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD)) {
3921 AliasDecl = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Complete);
3922 } else {
3923 const auto *CD = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD);
3924 AliasDecl = GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete);
3925 }
3926 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getFunctionLinkage(AliasDecl);
3927
3928 if (llvm::GlobalValue::isDiscardableIfUnused(Linkage))
3929 return StructorCodegen::RAUW;
3930
3931 // FIXME: Should we allow available_externally aliases?
3932 if (!llvm::GlobalAlias::isValidLinkage(Linkage))
3933 return StructorCodegen::RAUW;
3934
3935 if (llvm::GlobalValue::isWeakForLinker(Linkage)) {
3936 // Only ELF and wasm support COMDATs with arbitrary names (C5/D5).
3937 if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() ||
3938 CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatWasm())
3939 return StructorCodegen::COMDAT;
3940 return StructorCodegen::Emit;
3941 }
3942
3943 return StructorCodegen::Alias;
3944}
3945
3946static void emitConstructorDestructorAlias(CodeGenModule &CGM,
3947 GlobalDecl AliasDecl,
3948 GlobalDecl TargetDecl) {
3949 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getFunctionLinkage(AliasDecl);
3950
3951 StringRef MangledName = CGM.getMangledName(AliasDecl);
3952 llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = CGM.GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3953 if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration())
3954 return;
3955
3956 auto *Aliasee = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CGM.GetAddrOfGlobal(TargetDecl));
3957
3958 // Create the alias with no name.
3959 auto *Alias = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Linkage, "", Aliasee);
3960
3961 // Constructors and destructors are always unnamed_addr.
3962 Alias->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3963
3964 // Switch any previous uses to the alias.
3965 if (Entry) {
3966 assert(Entry->getType() == Aliasee->getType() &&
3967 "declaration exists with different type");
3968 Alias->takeName(Entry);
3969 Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(Alias);
3970 Entry->eraseFromParent();
3971 } else {
3972 Alias->setName(MangledName);
3973 }
3974
3975 // Finally, set up the alias with its proper name and attributes.
3976 CGM.SetCommonAttributes(AliasDecl, Alias);
3977}
3978
3979void ItaniumCXXABI::emitCXXStructor(GlobalDecl GD) {
3980 auto *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3981 auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD);
3982 const CXXDestructorDecl *DD = CD ? nullptr : cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD);
3983
3984 StructorCodegen CGType = getCodegenToUse(CGM, MD);
3985
3986 if (CD ? GD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Complete
3987 : GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete) {
3988 GlobalDecl BaseDecl;
3989 if (CD)
3990 BaseDecl = GD.getWithCtorType(Ctor_Base);
3991 else
3992 BaseDecl = GD.getWithDtorType(Dtor_Base);
3993
3994 if (CGType == StructorCodegen::Alias || CGType == StructorCodegen::COMDAT) {
3995 emitConstructorDestructorAlias(CGM, GD, BaseDecl);
3996 return;
3997 }
3998
3999 if (CGType == StructorCodegen::RAUW) {
4000 StringRef MangledName = CGM.getMangledName(GD);
4001 auto *Aliasee = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobal(BaseDecl);
4002 CGM.addReplacement(MangledName, Aliasee);
4003 return;
4004 }
4005 }
4006
4007 // The base destructor is equivalent to the base destructor of its
4008 // base class if there is exactly one non-virtual base class with a
4009 // non-trivial destructor, there are no fields with a non-trivial
4010 // destructor, and the body of the destructor is trivial.
4011 if (DD && GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base &&
4012 CGType != StructorCodegen::COMDAT &&
4013 !CGM.TryEmitBaseDestructorAsAlias(DD))
4014 return;
4015
4016 // FIXME: The deleting destructor is equivalent to the selected operator
4017 // delete if:
4018 // * either the delete is a destroying operator delete or the destructor
4019 // would be trivial if it weren't virtual,
4020 // * the conversion from the 'this' parameter to the first parameter of the
4021 // destructor is equivalent to a bitcast,
4022 // * the destructor does not have an implicit "this" return, and
4023 // * the operator delete has the same calling convention and IR function type
4024 // as the destructor.
4025 // In such cases we should try to emit the deleting dtor as an alias to the
4026 // selected 'operator delete'.
4027
4028 llvm::Function *Fn = CGM.codegenCXXStructor(GD);
4029
4030 if (CGType == StructorCodegen::COMDAT) {
4031 SmallString<256> Buffer;
4032 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
4033 if (DD)
4034 getMangleContext().mangleCXXDtorComdat(DD, Out);
4035 else
4036 getMangleContext().mangleCXXCtorComdat(CD, Out);
4037 llvm::Comdat *C = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Out.str());
4038 Fn->setComdat(C);
4039 } else {
4040 CGM.maybeSetTrivialComdat(*MD, *Fn);
4041 }
4042}

4068namespace {
4069 /// A cleanup to call __cxa_end_catch. In many cases, the caught
4070 /// exception type lets us state definitively that the thrown exception
4071 /// type does not have a destructor. In particular:
4072 /// - Catch-alls tell us nothing, so we have to conservatively
4073 /// assume that the thrown exception might have a destructor.
4074 /// - Catches by reference behave according to their base types.
4075 /// - Catches of non-record types will only trigger for exceptions
4076 /// of non-record types, which never have destructors.
4077 /// - Catches of record types can trigger for arbitrary subclasses
4078 /// of the caught type, so we have to assume the actual thrown
4079 /// exception type might have a throwing destructor, even if the
4080 /// caught type's destructor is trivial or nothrow.
4081 struct CallEndCatch final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
4082 CallEndCatch(bool MightThrow) : MightThrow(MightThrow) {}
4083 bool MightThrow;
4084
4085 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
4086 if (!MightThrow) {
4087 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getEndCatchFn(CGF.CGM));
4088 return;
4089 }
4090
4091 CGF.EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(getEndCatchFn(CGF.CGM));
4092 }
4093 };
4094}

4096/// Emits a call to __cxa_begin_catch and enters a cleanup to call
4097/// __cxa_end_catch.
4098///
4099/// \param EndMightThrow - true if __cxa_end_catch might throw
4100static llvm::Value *CallBeginCatch(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4101 llvm::Value *Exn,
4102 bool EndMightThrow) {
4103 llvm::CallInst *call =
4104 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getBeginCatchFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4105
4106 CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallEndCatch>(NormalAndEHCleanup, EndMightThrow);
4107
4108 return call;
4109}

4111/// A "special initializer" callback for initializing a catch
4112/// parameter during catch initialization.
4113static void InitCatchParam(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4114 const VarDecl &CatchParam,
4115 Address ParamAddr,
4116 SourceLocation Loc) {
4117 // Load the exception from where the landing pad saved it.
4118 llvm::Value *Exn = CGF.getExceptionFromSlot();
4119
4120 CanQualType CatchType =
4121 CGF.CGM.getContext().getCanonicalType(CatchParam.getType());
4122 llvm::Type *LLVMCatchTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(CatchType);
4123
4124 // If we're catching by reference, we can just cast the object
4125 // pointer to the appropriate pointer.
4126 if (isa<ReferenceType>(CatchType)) {
4127 QualType CaughtType = cast<ReferenceType>(CatchType)->getPointeeType();
4128 bool EndCatchMightThrow = CaughtType->isRecordType();
4129
4130 // __cxa_begin_catch returns the adjusted object pointer.
4131 llvm::Value *AdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, EndCatchMightThrow);
4132
4133 // We have no way to tell the personality function that we're
4134 // catching by reference, so if we're catching a pointer,
4135 // __cxa_begin_catch will actually return that pointer by value.
4136 if (const PointerType *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(CaughtType)) {
4137 QualType PointeeType = PT->getPointeeType();
4138
4139 // When catching by reference, generally we should just ignore
4140 // this by-value pointer and use the exception object instead.
4141 if (!PointeeType->isRecordType()) {
4142
4143 // Exn points to the struct _Unwind_Exception header, which
4144 // we have to skip past in order to reach the exception data.
4145 unsigned HeaderSize =
4146 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getSizeOfUnwindException();
4147 AdjustedExn = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(Exn, HeaderSize);
4148
4149 // However, if we're catching a pointer-to-record type that won't
4150 // work, because the personality function might have adjusted
4151 // the pointer. There's actually no way for us to fully satisfy
4152 // the language/ABI contract here: we can't use Exn because it
4153 // might have the wrong adjustment, but we can't use the by-value
4154 // pointer because it's off by a level of abstraction.
4155 //
4156 // The current solution is to dump the adjusted pointer into an
4157 // alloca, which breaks language semantics (because changing the
4158 // pointer doesn't change the exception) but at least works.
4159 // The better solution would be to filter out non-exact matches
4160 // and rethrow them, but this is tricky because the rethrow
4161 // really needs to be catchable by other sites at this landing
4162 // pad. The best solution is to fix the personality function.
4163 } else {
4164 // Pull the pointer for the reference type off.
4165 llvm::Type *PtrTy =
4166 cast<llvm::PointerType>(LLVMCatchTy)->getElementType();
4167
4168 // Create the temporary and write the adjusted pointer into it.
4169 Address ExnPtrTmp =
4170 CGF.CreateTempAlloca(PtrTy, CGF.getPointerAlign(), "exn.byref.tmp");
4171 llvm::Value *Casted = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, PtrTy);
4172 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Casted, ExnPtrTmp);
4173
4174 // Bind the reference to the temporary.
4175 AdjustedExn = ExnPtrTmp.getPointer();
4176 }
4177 }
4178
4179 llvm::Value *ExnCast =
4180 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, LLVMCatchTy, "exn.byref");
4181 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(ExnCast, ParamAddr);
4182 return;
4183 }
4184
4185 // Scalars and complexes.
4186 TypeEvaluationKind TEK = CGF.getEvaluationKind(CatchType);
4187 if (TEK != TEK_Aggregate) {
4188 llvm::Value *AdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, false);
4189
4190 // If the catch type is a pointer type, __cxa_begin_catch returns
4191 // the pointer by value.
4192 if (CatchType->hasPointerRepresentation()) {
4193 llvm::Value *CastExn =
4194 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, LLVMCatchTy, "exn.casted");
4195
4196 switch (CatchType.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime()) {
4197 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4198 CastExn = CGF.EmitARCRetainNonBlock(CastExn);
4199 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4200
4201 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4202 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4203 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4204 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(CastExn, ParamAddr);
4205 return;
4206
4207 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4208 CGF.EmitARCInitWeak(ParamAddr, CastExn);
4209 return;
4210 }
4211 llvm_unreachable("bad ownership qualifier!");
4212 }
4213
4214 // Otherwise, it returns a pointer into the exception object.
4215
4216 unsigned DefaultAS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
4217 llvm::Type *PtrTy = LLVMCatchTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
4218 llvm::Value *Cast = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(AdjustedExn, PtrTy);
4219
4220 LValue srcLV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(Cast, CatchType);
4221 LValue destLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ParamAddr, CatchType);
4222 switch (TEK) {
4223 case TEK_Complex:
4224 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(CGF.EmitLoadOfComplex(srcLV, Loc), destLV,
4225 /*init*/ true);
4226 return;
4227 case TEK_Scalar: {
4228 llvm::Value *ExnLoad = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(srcLV, Loc);
4229 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(ExnLoad, destLV, /*init*/ true);
4230 return;
4231 }
4232 case TEK_Aggregate:
4233 llvm_unreachable("evaluation kind filtered out!");
4234 }
4235 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
4236 }
4237
4238 assert(isa<RecordType>(CatchType) && "unexpected catch type!");
4239 auto catchRD = CatchType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4240 CharUnits caughtExnAlignment = CGF.CGM.getClassPointerAlignment(catchRD);
4241
4242 unsigned DefaultAS = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
4243 llvm::Type *PtrTy = LLVMCatchTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
4244
4245 // Check for a copy expression. If we don't have a copy expression,
4246 // that means a trivial copy is okay.
4247 const Expr *copyExpr = CatchParam.getInit();
4248 if (!copyExpr) {
4249 llvm::Value *rawAdjustedExn = CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4250 Address adjustedExn(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(rawAdjustedExn, PtrTy),
4251 caughtExnAlignment);
4252 LValue Dest = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ParamAddr, CatchType);
4253 LValue Src = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(adjustedExn, CatchType);
4254 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dest, Src, CatchType, AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
4255 return;
4256 }
4257
4258 // We have to call __cxa_get_exception_ptr to get the adjusted
4259 // pointer before copying.
4260 llvm::CallInst *rawAdjustedExn =
4261 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getGetExceptionPtrFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4262
4263 // Cast that to the appropriate type.
4264 Address adjustedExn(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(rawAdjustedExn, PtrTy),
4265 caughtExnAlignment);
4266
4267 // The copy expression is defined in terms of an OpaqueValueExpr.
4268 // Find it and map it to the adjusted expression.
4269 CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMapping
4270 opaque(CGF, OpaqueValueExpr::findInCopyConstruct(copyExpr),
4271 CGF.MakeAddrLValue(adjustedExn, CatchParam.getType()));
4272
4273 // Call the copy ctor in a terminate scope.
4274 CGF.EHStack.pushTerminate();
4275
4276 // Perform the copy construction.
4277 CGF.EmitAggExpr(copyExpr,
4278 AggValueSlot::forAddr(ParamAddr, Qualifiers(),
4279 AggValueSlot::IsNotDestructed,
4280 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
4281 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
4282 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
4283
4284 // Leave the terminate scope.
4285 CGF.EHStack.popTerminate();
4286
4287 // Undo the opaque value mapping.
4288 opaque.pop();
4289
4290 // Finally we can call __cxa_begin_catch.
4291 CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4292}

4294/// Begins a catch statement by initializing the catch variable and
4295/// calling __cxa_begin_catch.
4296void ItaniumCXXABI::emitBeginCatch(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4297 const CXXCatchStmt *S) {
4298 // We have to be very careful with the ordering of cleanups here:
4299 // C++ [except.throw]p4:
4300 // The destruction [of the exception temporary] occurs
4301 // immediately after the destruction of the object declared in
4302 // the exception-declaration in the handler.
4303 //
4304 // So the precise ordering is:
4305 // 1. Construct catch variable.
4306 // 2. __cxa_begin_catch
4307 // 3. Enter __cxa_end_catch cleanup
4308 // 4. Enter dtor cleanup
4309 //
4310 // We do this by using a slightly abnormal initialization process.
4311 // Delegation sequence:
4312 // - ExitCXXTryStmt opens a RunCleanupsScope
4313 // - EmitAutoVarAlloca creates the variable and debug info
4314 // - InitCatchParam initializes the variable from the exception
4315 // - CallBeginCatch calls __cxa_begin_catch
4316 // - CallBeginCatch enters the __cxa_end_catch cleanup
4317 // - EmitAutoVarCleanups enters the variable destructor cleanup
4318 // - EmitCXXTryStmt emits the code for the catch body
4319 // - EmitCXXTryStmt close the RunCleanupsScope
4320
4321 VarDecl *CatchParam = S->getExceptionDecl();
4322 if (!CatchParam) {
4323 llvm::Value *Exn = CGF.getExceptionFromSlot();
4324 CallBeginCatch(CGF, Exn, true);
4325 return;
4326 }
4327
4328 // Emit the local.
4329 CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission var = CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(*CatchParam);
4330 InitCatchParam(CGF, *CatchParam, var.getObjectAddress(CGF), S->getBeginLoc());
4331 CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(var);
4332}

4334/// Get or define the following function:
4335/// void @__clang_call_terminate(i8* %exn) nounwind noreturn
4336/// This code is used only in C++.
4337static llvm::FunctionCallee getClangCallTerminateFn(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
4338 llvm::FunctionType *fnTy =
4339 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, CGM.Int8PtrTy, /*IsVarArgs=*/false);
4340 llvm::FunctionCallee fnRef = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
4341 fnTy, "__clang_call_terminate", llvm::AttributeList(), /*IsLocal=*/true);
4342 llvm::Function *fn =
4343 cast<llvm::Function>(fnRef.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts());
4344 if (fn->empty()) {
4345 fn->setDoesNotThrow();
4346 fn->setDoesNotReturn();
4347
4348 // What we really want is to massively penalize inlining without
4349 // forbidding it completely. The difference between that and
4350 // 'noinline' is negligible.
4351 fn->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
4352
4353 // Allow this function to be shared across translation units, but
4354 // we don't want it to turn into an exported symbol.
4355 fn->setLinkage(llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
4356 fn->setVisibility(llvm::Function::HiddenVisibility);
4357 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
4358 fn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(fn->getName()));
4359
4360 // Set up the function.
4361 llvm::BasicBlock *entry =
4362 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "", fn);
4363 CGBuilderTy builder(CGM, entry);
4364
4365 // Pull the exception pointer out of the parameter list.
4366 llvm::Value *exn = &*fn->arg_begin();
4367
4368 // Call __cxa_begin_catch(exn).
4369 llvm::CallInst *catchCall = builder.CreateCall(getBeginCatchFn(CGM), exn);
4370 catchCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4371 catchCall->setCallingConv(CGM.getRuntimeCC());
4372
4373 // Call std::terminate().
4374 llvm::CallInst *termCall = builder.CreateCall(CGM.getTerminateFn());
4375 termCall->setDoesNotThrow();
4376 termCall->setDoesNotReturn();
4377 termCall->setCallingConv(CGM.getRuntimeCC());
4378
4379 // std::terminate cannot return.
4380 builder.CreateUnreachable();
4381 }
4382 return fnRef;
4383}

4385llvm::CallInst *
4386ItaniumCXXABI::emitTerminateForUnexpectedException(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4387 llvm::Value *Exn) {
4388 // In C++, we want to call __cxa_begin_catch() before terminating.
4389 if (Exn) {
4390 assert(CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
4391 return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getClangCallTerminateFn(CGF.CGM), Exn);
4392 }
4393 return CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGF.CGM.getTerminateFn());
4394}
